house. Yes. Yes. Yes, and a man by the name of Duncan used to be there then, Mr Dunkley.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did your mother make her own bread?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No. No, not her bread, no, only cake. Dough buns or - or dough - dough cakes she used to make.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Was this the Portland dough}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8598532\charrsid16449734 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 cake?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Yes. Yes. It's hard work making dough cakes. Ever such hard work, because you've got to - you get your dough - people still make dough
 cakes now. You go to the - the bake house and you say - two pound of dough. And - you take it home and you put it in a cloth and put it so that it rised up. Keep it in a - same temperature. Then you get your lard, pound of lard, and you've got to knead a
ll that lard into that flour - into that dough until it comes out all - sticky you know, all in threads. Oh it is hard work. I've done it - but it's my hand - it makes your hands - ache, kneading the dough like this.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 It's a very old recipe then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Oh gosh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 So your mother bought the bread normally then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Oh yes, she bought her bread.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did she make jam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No, she didn't do any preserves like that at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No bottled fruit or vegetables or anything?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No, no, no. Nothing like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 You didn't have a garden did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
Well we had an allotment where the - where the - Coronation Road is now it was all allotments. And we had allotment, but it was all potatoes and cabbage and things like that you know, and beetroot and - and - things for the house you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Who looked after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 My father. Potatoes and cabbage, beans, peas, we used to have a - everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Do you remember your mother making any pickles?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No, she never did -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Or any wine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No, she never did anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did she make any medicines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
No. No. No. The only thing that she did once - was - she got - went to - Preston, that was her home, and somebody gave her some herbs and - before - sort of - toothache and th
ings like that and she just - boiled that down and put the solution into a - you know when it cooled she put it into - sort of bottles. And - it was sort of a - it wasn't very - nothing very much really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 You just remember this on one occasion?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 O
n one occasion. I remember her bringing it back and saying - oh this is - I must do this, I must boil this down and put it in some bottles because it's very good for toothache, and I can remember her saying it. But - that was the only thing that ever I kn
ew she did. She was a big church worker -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Do you remember having it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
No, I didn't have any. She was a big church worker my mother was. She used to - with the teas and the bazaars and that, did all the teas in the - when they had bazaars. St. - St
 Johns. And she made - they had a - down where the - picture palace was now they}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8598532\charrsid16449734  had a big sort of a garden fet }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
thing down there, a bazaar, and she made some hollyhocks, that big. You know, paper hollyhocks.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 What time of year did they have this bazaar then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
Oh - I suppose about June I suppose, it is now you see we've got one in a fortnight's time, our bazaar, well it's about the same time you see that follows on every year. This festival thing.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 This is the same tradition then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 My mother did it. My sister did it. And I do it -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Do you make the hollyhocks still?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
No, I don't make the hollyhocks, no fear. I help, I - I - see, I - now Wednesday I shall be up there about - I suppose about two o'clock. I can't go up in the - in the 
morning to help because I'm working. About two o'clock and I take over and I pour tea from about three o'clock until six continually. I do the pouring. Somebody else takes the money. I have nothing to do with any money. Then if anything goes wrong I'm not
 in it. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did your mother go to church with you then, you went to chapel then didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Chapel, yes, we went to chapel. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did your mother go to chapel with you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No, we went on our own, no, we went on our - we went on our o
wn to church for a long time but she used to go sometimes but not very often but she used to do - all the church work you know - at one time she used to clean the church hall. They - you know, like when - parsh room as we call it. You see, she used to do 
that one time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Was that when your father was out of work again?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No, my father - doing something for the church, yes. She never got - didn't get paid for it. No, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 What other things did she do for the church then, did she go regularly to any meetings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
No - oh used to go to the meetings, to the Mother's Meetings and things like that. Like - it's - what is it, the Mother's Guild isn't it. I think the Mother's Union, that's right, Mother's Union. She went - belonged to that, I belong}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8598532\charrsid16449734  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 to that, I go every - third Tuesday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 You remember her going to that when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
Oh no, I - I - not so much when I was a little girl because - she never - she wouldn't - she didn't do the church so much, she didn't do so much then it w
as - after I was married. She - went - she took over, because - I don't know, Marion, my younger sister, she used to go with her and used to go everywhere with her. Marion used to. But of course I mean I don't - Iris - I don't think Iris ever - she didn't
 go to church at all, Iris didn't. But she wasn't a bad girl but she never used to go to church like we did, like I used to.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Iris was much younger wasn't she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 So your mother wasn't actually going out to church while you were small?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
Oh no, no, no. No. Oh no. She never went out in the evening. She was always there. If she went out anywhere for a walk and that we always went with her if - if she went out anywhere. Sometimes she used to go down - on the - it was no sea wall there you 
know, it was just on the beach. If she used to take a walk along the cliff we'd go down there but very very rarely. We were nearly always used to stay round about the house playing you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did your father brew any beer for the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did they drink in fact?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 My father used to have a glass of beer occasionally but he never - used to get drunk or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did he go to the pub then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Oh yes. Yes. Now my grandma - I tell you - when I was - how old was I - abo
ut twelve or thirteen I suppose - oh she must have been - must have been going on a long time before that, but I can particularly remember - you know they used to wear the capes, the old ladies, and a little bonnet with a - rose in the - or something in t
h
e front, and tied under the chin? Well she used to - put her cloak on, take her little jug, go down what is the St ar now, used to be the Prince of Wales. Go down there and get a - half a pint of stout. Go home, take her bit of cheese, and she used to go 
d
own to a friend's called Mrs Tizzard, Emma, we used to call her. And she used to take her - her bread and cheese and her half a pint of stout down there and have that there with Emma. And I can see her now. With her cloak and her little jug you know. No. 
No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did your mother have to buy any vegetables or did your father grow enough?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
Oh well - well - not - when they weren't very - when - like in between times. She had to buy vegetables then. And - but - nearly always there was always - - potatoes a
nd that. But very rarely had to buy - a lot. Only in between times when - was growing sort of things and - like it is now. I mean, there the broad beans are coming in, well - we never bought broad beans because they were too expensive. We waited until we 
had our own. Sort of thing. Lettuce, radishes, and things like that he never grew tomatoes. But radishes and - and lettuce, plenty of.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Do you remember having fruit as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Yes, we had plenty of apples. Because - my mother's home was in Prest
on and they had a - an orchard there, you see, so that we could always get apples. Oranges - Christmastime, you might get one occasionally in and out you know, but Christmastime we always had an orange and apple and nuts in our stockings. Always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did your mother buy any tinned fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Yes, pineapple. Because it was cheap then, you now, pears and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Would this be for a special Sunday tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Oh - yes, well sometimes - in the week sometimes we - if we were lucky we'd get it. And - she used to
 make a lot of - jellies and blancmanges for us you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did she use dried vegetables or dried fruit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Well - what for - what do you mean? Oh no, no vegetables, you - you didn't get those vegetables like you do now you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 They used to have peas didn't they, dried peas?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
Yes. Peas. Dried peas, yes, and things like that, yes, butter beans, haricot beans and things like that. She used to make - I tell you she used to - what she used to do sometimes and that was to get a - a hock of baco
n. And - put it in a pot, in the oven, with a lid on, and put the haricot beans in with it. Nice that is. And she - I'll tell you another thing she did with - to bakes jam roly-poly pudding, in a jam jar. In a stone jam jar, you don't see them now. You kn
ow, in a stone jam - she used to have a big one like that and she used to make a suet pudding, jam suet pudding, grease it, put it in the oven, put a piece of grease}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8598532\charrsid16449734 -pro}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 of on the top there and bake it like - oh it's beautiful.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 People don't make suet puddings very much these days do they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 And if they only did but know it how }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8598532\charrsid16449734 nutritious}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734  it is, it's far better than all this - fancy stuff you know. You make a suet pudding - with jam or treacle - on it, and - it's very}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8598532\charrsid16449734 
 filling and it's very nutritious}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 .
 Yes. And it's fat and that. Don't you ever make it? Yes. I'll tell you what though. My mother used to make a - a rhubarb syrup, rhubarb pudding and - and - apple pudding. With custard. Cheap. An}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8598532\charrsid16449734 d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734  good. You know how it's done do you? No, no, no, no. You ge
t the - you - you make your suet, you make a - you put your suet in your flour and your salt. Mix it all up together and you roll it out. And you cut your apple - or }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8598532\charrsid16449734 rhubarb}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734  or whatever it is, you put it in the centre. Sprinkle it with brown sugar, and wra
p it all up and put it in a cloth and boil it for about an hour and a quarter. And it's beautiful. You get all the juices - all sealed in. And then when you open it it's all steaming and all - beautiful. And have cream or - and it's ever so cheap. Well, I
 don't know about the apples, I - they're - they're a bit expensive now but I mean your flour and your syrup, you could get - and - and it's a beautiful thing wintertime for - tea or something like that. Very warming you know. No. They don't, no.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 You see suet in very little packets, you must have bought large quantities in those days?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
I never - I never buy packet suet. I always go to the butchers and get a piece of suet. I go the butchers and I say, I want a quarter of suet please George. And - I take it - he says, do you want it grated? Yes please. It's already grated.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Do you remember buying it like this for your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Yes, dozens of times. That's what I say about these cuttings, I went into the butchers and asked him if he - I said,
 don't you ever have any cutting now George? And he said, cuttings? I said, beef cuttings, all the bits off the beef, I said, that - he said, that's all used up for different things ma'am, he said, you never - get anything like that. We used to get - a sh
illings worth, be enough for the family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did your father keep any hens or pigs or goats or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No, no. There was nowhere to keep it. You see, you weren't allowed to keep anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did you have meat every day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No, about three or four times a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did your mother buy any tinned meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
No. Bacon, used to get - have bacon. Got egg and bacon for tea or something like that. Of course it was cheaper then see, bacon. I can remember buying back bacon for ninepence a pound. Best back bacon. Streaky five}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid8598532\charrsid16449734  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 pence. Collar seven}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8598532\charrsid16449734  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
pence. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 You had more bacon than other meat then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Oh - no, we used to vary you know, and - we used to have liver and bacon. As I say, these meat pies. Or we used to have stew, p
lenty of stews. My mother used to get a sheep}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8598532\charrsid16449734 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
s head for one and six. Half a sheep - half a bull - bullocks head, one and six. And she used to put it in soak overnight with salt water. Cut all the meat off. And make a pie one day and stew the next for one 
and six for a family. With - onions, all the vegetables - carrots, swede, dumplings, you know. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 I suppose you had fish as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Oh yes, we had - used to have a lot of fish, 'cos we could go over the beach and get the fish. Not like it is no
w you know. You could go over the beach any time and get mackerel or whiting or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 People who caught them would sell them you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Sell them to you, yes. When I was about - eight or nine years old I used to go - over the beach
 and when the mackerel strand, you know what they call strand, and get the mackerel - boats come in. I'd take home about fifty little tiny ones on a string. My mother used to put 'em in salt. Salt - salt them down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 She didn't do any pickling but she used to do salt fish?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
Oh no - great earthenware pans you know. And - put a sprinkle of salt at the bottom, you know, and salt it down there and then put it down and then - when there was no fish about see we had to do was to take it out and soak it an
d - we had a mackerel. And they were little tiny ones, they are the best you know. Those little tiny ones, haymakers. Haven't you? Oh yes, you get them about that big. Oh they're lovely and sweet. They're the best ones than those big ones. They're ever so
 sweet and we - we used to have a lot soused you know, in the vinegar. And bay leaves. We used to do a lot of that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did you ever get any extra meat such as - did people keep bunnies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Oh yes, and they used to go out and catch them. I used to - I u
sed to know somebody who used to catch them and that and we used to buy them for about - sixpence each. Nine}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8598532\charrsid16449734  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
pence. During the first world war - how old was I then, 1914-1918. Fourteen. I used to go out - we couldn't get any meat. And I used to get up at f
our o'clock in the morning and go out the - Weymouth Road, and meet the man coming in - with bunnies, and we used to pay nine}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid8598532\charrsid16449734  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
pence each for them. But you had to go out and get them otherwise you'd never get any when you - time you come in the square, they'd be all gone.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 So they didn't in fact come from Portland?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No, no, oh no, out in the country. Oh gosh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 People keep them here don't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 They keep them as pets for meat don't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Yes. Oh yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did they do that then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
No, no, no, no. More recent - yes, that - this is more recent. I mean - there was so many about you see, the - and that myxymotosis wasn't even invented then, so that was - right out of the question, people - never thought about, you
 know, doing that sort of thing. But people are a bit dubious, they're not now but they were a bit dubious about eating bunnies after that you know. But - there's stacks of them round again. You go down to Castletown at night time, when I used to go babys
itting for Captain Morrison's wife, and you look out the back just now, there's stacks of them running around. Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Portland people have got a thing about bunnies though haven't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Yes, well now that originated from a - crane breakin
g and - the - the bunnies burrowing underneath - weakening the crane, someone was killed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 This was how it originated?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Yes, how it origin - so they say, but I mean I can't remember, I don't know. But if a quarryman is going to work in the morning
, and a bunny runs across his path he goes back. He won't go to work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 It was because of a crane accident?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
Well it - it - they said it was but whether it's true or not I don't know 'cos I wasn't - but it was through the bunnies burrowing underneath that weakened the - shafts and that, weakened it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 They would eat bunnies?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
Yes, but you don't - daren't say the word bunny in front of 'em. I remember I was working up - how old would I have been then - I think I was waiting for the home help 
job. It was since I've been back from South Africa. I was working in a hospital. And then - I was working up the castle. And somebody said rabbit in the - in the - kitchen, and the cook - downed tools you know. She finished. 'Til next day, she wouldn't wo
rk. Oh yes. I reckon it's stupid. Superstition I suppose. Yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did your father have more to eat then the rest of you, do you remember your mother specially giving him extra?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Well I think - she used to dish his dinner out first and s
ee that he had plenty. You know. I mean - his dinner was always there - when he came home from work. And - she used to dish his dinner as I say and see that he had plenty. And - there was - then of course my brother, when he started work, when he was a yo
ung lad he started work, he used to - have a - a fair amount. But we weren't - we didn't - we - well I never say we didn't go hungry. Ida, Joe and I - know - knew what it was to be hungry.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 You're thinking of the time when your father was out of work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
Out of work, yes. The others - he was in work and - there was money coming in - when the others came along sort of thing. But we were the ones that - had the pinch you know. Like having bread and butter for - having a piece of bread and butter and ja
m for breakfast and a piece of bread and butter and jam for tea. All that sort of thing you know. And - just enough dinner for the men that were working you know, and - and might be a little bit left and - all that sort of thing. But we survived.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Do you remember your mother not having anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
Oh mum - oh mum's been without, yes, mum's been without lots of times, I know that, she'd been out lots of times without for us kids. And I'll tell you another thing she's done. When she couldn't afford to
 buy any underclothes she's - cut up material and made underclothes for us. Pants and - petticoats. You know. 'Cos she was very good in that way. She used to make a lot of things. Lot of dresses and that for us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 That was all done by hand I suppose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No, machine, she had a machine, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Was it a hand one or a treadle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Hand, yes, hand. I couldn't get on with a treadle, I had a treadle, I gave it to my daughter. I couldn't get on with the treadle.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 In the evening when your father was back did you all sit round the table and have your meal together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Oh yes. Yes. Sat down together, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Were you allowed to talk during meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Well - mum used to say, get on with your food, get on with your dinner or whatever you were h
aving, get on with it. And that sort you know but - we - could sort of - she didn't like it but if we chipped in once now and then - couldn't do much about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did they have a conversation then and you try and join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Oh no. No fear. They were 
- my mum - of course - you see, my dad - he was a - a man like this, if my mother said to Mrs So and so said so and so Jim, he said - Eva, I don't want to hear anything about it and it's nothing to do with you. And that was that. He wouldn't listen to gos
sip. No, he wouldn't listen. And I never - do you know I never heard my father swear but once. That was somebody upset him and he just let rip then but that was the only time. Never used to swear. And my mum never used to - never used to drink.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Could you choose what you wanted to eat from what was cooked?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No. No. Eat it or go without. Eat it or go without, that was it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 She put it on your plate and you had to eat it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Yes. Yes. No - you couldn't say, oh I don't like this. Daren't say tha
t. Oh I don't like this. She'd just put it down and - eat it and if you didn't like it you left it and - that was that, you went without.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Could you leave something if you didn't like it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 If you didn't want it, yes, but you didn't have anything else in replace. It was either eat it or go without.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 If you left some dinner would you be allowed some pudding afterwards then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Oh yes, she'd say - well she might say - why didn't you want that? I don't want - didn't want it and that and say - ha
ven't got room for that haven't got room for anything else. But she used to give it to us you know. If she had it. It was a - it was a question of whether she had it or not. I mean - I tell you what we used to have though - with - my mum used to say - I'l
l
 give you some cheese on toast. And we used to have cheese on toast for tea. Well that was nice, we used to enjoy it. And that wasn't very expensive you see. But it was always good. You see, she used to try and do the - get round the cheapest way - and al
so - something which would fill us up and do us good. That was difficult. It was difficult, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 If there was something on the table you wanted, like the salt, could you ask somebody to pass it to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Or did you have to wait until it was offered?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
No, you'd say, could I have the salt or - you know, can - will you pass the salt and that and that was all right. No, oh yes, we were allowed to ask for things like that. And we were allowed to ask for a piece of bread if we wanted it.
 Say, mummy can I have a piece of bread and butter, or whatever it was. Or - or - we used to say - is there another cake to spare? 'Cos mum used to make a lot of little ones you know. And she'll say - just wait a minute, if somebody else had - hadn't had 
any you must wait, you know, sort of thing.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 If there was some extra could you ask for some more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
Oh yes, it was very - yes, if there was - if anybody - everybody had had a helping and there was any over and they'd say - mummy can I have somethin
g, and she'd say yes. If - when it was there, and everybody had had a helping, if there was any over you could have it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Could you take a book to the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 NO. No. Gosh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 When could you leave the table, did you have to wait?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No, wel
l if - if - we finished our meal, we'd say, mummy can we get down? She might, say, yes, or she might say, well, wait until the others are finished. All depends how she felt. But we - oh yes, always had to ask.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 You didn't always have to wait until everybody had finished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No. No, we could get down and - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did you always have the same place at the table?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Well, near enough the same place. Yes. And we knew where we were then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did your mother always serve the meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Yes. Yes. Always carved too, my - my dad would never carve - she always used to cut up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did she have a special order in which she served you - she served your father first?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 First, and then my brother sand and that and then - well I suppose as she went - we 
went round she - because she used to serve at the table you see. What she used to do was to - cook her potatoes, cook all her food and that and strain it up, and it used to be in vegetable dishes then, you know. Not like it is now, I mean, I've got vegeta
b
le dishes at home but I never use them. Not unless I've got anybody coming, I mean to say - you see, I - I - I'm - we - feed in the kitchen, my little kitchen with having the - very seldom anybody else you see. When Hazel's down and - and the children wel
l we can get round, we've just got enough room to get round. When we - when I serve from the - kitchen, you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Do you remember who fed your younger brothers and sisters when they were small, did your mother do it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Well - we - I - I think I can
 remember - occasionally that I used to feed the little ones you know. Feed them if mum was busy. And of course - if they were bottle fed it was - a case of - taking the baby and feeding it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Would you have helped with that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Yes. Yes. Yes. Little ones. Babies. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Would your mother have done the bottle then just given it to you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Just given it to us, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Do you remember having to change their nappies or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No, not as we - not when we were tiny - I don't think I've ever changed a babies nappy when - when they were -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did you have to take them out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Oh yes. Take them out. Get quite cross too 'cos I had to them out. Take them out in a pram.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Where would you have taken them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Down the park. Nowhere else to take them you see. Just down the park.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did your mother have a pram then to put them in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
Yes, oh yes, we had prams you know. Of course they were - not like they are now, they were - we had - a deep one, you know, like a box one you k
now. Oh funny. I remember rocking my - I don't know whether - one of the - whether it was Iris or - must have been Iris, or John. I remember - it must have been Iris I think, rocking her in the rocking - chair, in a - in a cradle. Rocking her and rocking 
her out on the floor. Because I was cross, 'cos I was cross 'cos I had to stop and look after her. Rocking here away and getting so wild and poor little thing was out.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 You must have been about nine then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 I wasn't very old. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Could you talk to your mother if you were bothered about anything, was she an easy person to talk to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Yes, she - she would listen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did you go to her?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 YES. Yes, she would listen. And she would - she would tell you, you know, certain - tell you, you kno
w, certain - tell you whether it was right or wrong, you know, she would say - oh you mustn't do this because it's not very nice or something like that, she would listen. And you came - you could go to her with all your troubles. And she would, you know, 
sort of do what she could.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Would she be affectionate then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Oh yes, yes. Yes.-
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did you go to your father if you were bothered about anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No, it was all - always mum. I mean, we used to talk to him and play - sit on his knee sometim
es but - but - if we wanted anything or wanted to do anything or - wanted to know about anything, we used to go and ask her you know. You know, sort of - tell you we were never allowed to do any sewing or knitting Sundays. That was a forbidden thing.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Was there anything else you weren't allowed to do on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No, only sew - she used to say - you can put that away, there's five days or six days in the week to do that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Were there any rules about Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Were you allowed to go out and play with your friends on Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
No, no, go for a walk. Weren't to go out to play. No, no, you mustn't go and play, you go - go for a walk and come home and - stop in or - have your friends in. My mums was terrible like that - she used to sa
y - you can have your friends in, 'cos we - only had a little room but we had a piano and - and somebody could play and have a little sing-song - you know. Yes. Oh - if you went out for your meals you were for it. Weren't allowed to - come in any time for
 your meals. Had to be there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did you have to behave towards your brothers and sisters in any particular way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No, not really. I don't - I don't think, because we were - we were a family as I say I was - not very friendly with my brother Joe - Har
ry, but that was a growing up period that was a period I was going through. Because afterwards there wasn't anybody - like him. And we were all - affectionate - we were all a good family you know. We were never quarrelling, we never quarrelled. Not as - c
h
ildren, like you know we bickered at one another and say, oh - where did you get that or - I haven't got something like it and that, but - on the whole we were a good family really. Affectionate family. We are now you know, we're very close now. Yes, but 
w
e are. I go down every day to see my sister. And if I don't go down she thinks I'm ill. My brother goes in every day. My other sister on the top here, we don't see her but she phones up every day. Yes. And my other brother only lives round the corner to m
y sister and - she sees him when he comes home from work and - he looks across - all right, and - you know. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did your mother tell you to hit back if another child hurt you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 NO. No. She'd say - she used to say to us - if - like if we had a qu
arrel outside you know, like children, she'll say, I'll not take any notice of you, you've got your - have your arms round one another tomorrow. You know, sort of - but it it was anything very serious she'd say - all right - if they come to me I shall exp
l
ain or - if they want to know what's happened or anything like that, she said, but don't take it into your own hands, she said, because - she said, it can cause more trouble than that. You know, she would never let us - I remember once - a girl hit - Iris
 
I think it was, and she was a little bit delinquent you know. And the mother came down and - no, it wasn't it was the - a man came and he said, Mrs Gail, the person is very concerned because - she - I - this Mabel, no - Ofield I think her name was, anyway
 
- Annie - Annie Ofield, she hit Iris and - and the mother was afraid - was afraid that - my mother would take it further, you see, and - she said, no, she said - I quite understand the position, I - I wouldn't like to be in the same position myself, you k
n
ow, as regards the other mother, she said. She said, she hasn't hurt her very much, she said, she'll soon get over it. But - and the mother was ever so pleased to think that my mother didn't take action, you know, that sort of thing. That's the sort of pe
rson she was, she would never - let us - fight or quarrel. Because she said there's no good got by it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Some children were told to sort their own problems out weren't they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Yes, well - that's all wrong because - I mean they - they've got no idea -
 what sorting out problems means and therefore they're going to - go to the extreme aren't they.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 What kind of people do you think your parents hoped you'd grown up to be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Well - as far as I know - the same as them, as straight - and - you know, everything above board.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 This is what they considered important in life, being straight?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
Oh yes, yes. Yes. And my - my brother told a lie once and he never told one afterwards, he wasn't very old. He'd said - somebody had sent him for some shoppi
ng and he said it was - a penny dearer than it was and he kept the penny. And he had the biggest hiding ever he had in his life and he never did it afterwards. And he's one of the nicest - I mean, he's my brother, but he's one of the nicest fellows that y
o
u - could meet. Straight. My mum - my father was very straight you know. He would never - now - he was - working - for a man called Mr Patten. Did I tell you? Yes. YES. Now I told you about the wood, did I - when he had to do a job. Well, he had to do a j
o
b for - this man, and he had to use old timber. Shave it up and make it look like new, and do you know, my father was so upset over it, he said, well, he said, I don't know how he thinks he's going to get on in this world when he does a thing like that. H
e said, I - he's charge - charging top price for old material I've used. Now that was the kind of man my father was. And that's the kind of thing that he did you see. And he had to do it because it was his job. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 What did your parents think of swearing then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No, they didn't - they never swore. Wouldn't allow us to swear either. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 When your mother was talking to somebody, you mentioned you weren't allowed to join in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Yes. No fear. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Could you wait until the conversation had finished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
No, you weren't allowed - to be near. If - she - if she was talking to a - there used to be a Mrs White used to live down below us and - she used to - she called her one day and - to ask her about something, I don't know what it was, and - 
I can remember distinctly - my mother going to the door and - and talking to Mrs White and I going down there, and she'd say - she said, did I send for you? No mummy. Well - go. Just like that. And - and - and - you - you didn't - you couldn't stand even 
a little way away. Right out the way. Then when she comes in she'll say - let me catch you coming like that - that again when I'm talking to anybody, she said, and you'll be the - it'll be the worse for you. You know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 When you were punished for doing things like this what did you feel about it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
Well we just had to take it. I mean - it's no good resenting it because it had to be done and - my mother had to - she took full control, as I said, it's no good - talking to my father. I mean, he was good 
and all that and he - he wouldn't go against mum. But at the same time he was so - too lenient because we could twist him round our little fingers if we wanted to, if mother didn't intervene.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 What did you feel when you used to get the cane?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Used to think she was the worst mother on earth I suppose. Couldn't - couldn't do this and couldn't do that. YES.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
Would you say that you received the ideas about how you should behave from both your parents or do you think one of them played a more important in this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
Well I should imagine that - my mother played the important part because therefore she - she had to - do the cling, I mean - if she was lenient where would we have been. I mean we would have done just what we liked. And there was a case 
of not having - not being able to. Mind you she wasn't a wicked mother and she wasn't cruel. You know, but she made us do as - as she - we - we were told, and the question of - it's no good me - letting you have your own way, your father doesn't do anythi
n
g. See? I know - she - I know he - she - once we - 'cos we - we were tickled to death over it because - she said, Jim, see to these children. And they - he said, hello. Now what could you do. And she said, oh you are a fool. So what could you do with a ma
n like that. I mean he - he wasn't aggressive. He was ever so kind and - and gentle, but - of course that started us off, we tickled - that tickled us. Mother was a bit riled about it but -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 When you had a birthday would it be different from any other day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did you have any presents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
Well, now - if we had a birthday, we might get - a handkerchief. Or - a box of sweets or something like that, but nothing very elaborate. Now Christmastime - my father was out of work - one Christmast
ime. We didn't have a Christmas dinner. Well, we didn't - we did have but - we weren't - mum didn't have enough money to buy anything. And - my father's brother, my Uncle Joe, he provided us with - a Christmas beef and he also bought a present for each of
 
us, and I remember mine was a little work box, full of cottons and silks and a thimble and that. And that was the only Christmas present we had, if it hadn't have been for him we wouldn't have had any. But Christmas - normal time - normal - what - but - o
h
 wait a minute, she might say - my mum might say, oh well you ban have Kitty in for - for tea and - she used to make a special little cake or something like that, but nothing very - not like they do now, go out and have a good time and - you know, all the
se -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 But your birthday would be remembered?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Oh remembered, yes. Yes, remembered. I remember once having a - a purse. You know, thought it was wonderful.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Can you remember anything that you did with your mother and father together on Christmas
 Day? Was there anything you all did together as a family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Well no, I - I think we just had our meal you know, Christmas meal and a tea. And I - I really think that - we all stayed in you know.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 You mentioned you had a piano, would you have everybody singing around the piano?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
Might have done, might have had a - someone in - playing the piano. I used to have a girl friend who used to come down and play - piano sometimes and might have had a sing-song like that. And - Boxing Day, we used to - 
more like - you know, sort of - go out for a walk or somewhere like that. Nothing very elaborate. Because there was no - nothing like it is now - I mean you can go to a club now and - have a dance and a sing-song like that, but there wasn't anything like 
that you see there.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Would you see anything or your relatives at Christmastime then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 What my uncles and aunties and - no, I don't think so, I think we were more or less - on our own you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 So there wasn't really anything different at Christmas except for the food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
No, just dinner that's all, that - no, nothing very different, no. Of course you see my mum's brothers - my mum's sisters were living at Preston. You see, and they used to have their little families and that and - my - I te
ll you fair time, when Portland fair, my mum's sisters - used to come in for Portland fair and stay the night in Preston. 'Cos that was the event then you know. See? But nothing very elaborate, never - used to make much difference.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 What would you have for Christmas dinner, do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
Oh beef, and pork. No chicken or anything like that. Might - oh, my - my dad did, he brought home a cockerel once, I remember - and - and I remember him saying - it was live and he had it in the yard. And I rem
ember him saying, I've - I've killed the cockerel Eva. And he couldn't have got up the top of the road and the thing crowed. She said, your father. So she had to get somebody else to do it. I remember that time, that -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Was this because he just couldn't do it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No, he thought he - whether he didn't - weak hearted perhaps, I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Was there anything else particular about Christmas, did you ever see crackers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Oh we had crackers and - at teatime you know and hats and that. And we had 
jelly and blancmange and all the - Christmas fare. Nuts and oranges - and all that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did you have your stocking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Oh yes, had stocking up and - filled that with - as I say, orange and apple and - and nuts. And sweets. And - I remember having a dol
l once you know. Stuck in the top. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did either your father or your mother play the piano?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did any of your children?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 I - I learnt - my sister learnt, I learnt for two and a half years, my brother plays - a bit.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 How old were you when you learnt to play, did you go to lessons?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 What were you, about seven?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Seven or eight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did you go to Fortunes Well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 I went to a Mrs Pope. Down next door to the Primitive chapel. Miss Pope, not Mrs Pope, Miss Pope.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Were there any other musical instruments in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did you have sort of musical sessions apart from when your friends came in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No. I used to just go in there and tinker, play the piano a bit but nothing - you know - not to entertain or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did anyone in the family sing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did you really ever get together as a family and sing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Sunday nights sometimes we used to have a - a little session, not very often because - if anyone ca
me in - now when my sister - before my sister was married, long time before she was married, she used to have lots of friends and they used to have a - a fellow by the name of Stone, he - he was popular fellow and he used to come and play the piano someti
mes. Then we used to have a sing-song but - not very often. Not very often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Were there any books in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Oh yes, well - we used to buy - what do you call it, comics and things like that but there - there weren't - not many reading - you kno
w library books or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did your parents have a bookcase with books in it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No. No. No, no. No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did your father have a newspaper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Oh he used to have a - Daily Chronicle every day. He'd sit and - sit and read after his -
 after his meal, you know, after his tea, used to put his - feet up on a - used to have a little black box and a cushion on the top and he used to bring that in and put his feet up and read the paper. Then he used to say, well I think I'd better go and se
e me father now, and then that was that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Were you allowed to look at the newspaper when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No. We never had the newspaper. Never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 You weren't allowed to look at it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No, well it wasn't a case of not looking at it, we weren't interested I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Were there any magazines?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 You mentioned the comics, you bought those yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Oh yes, you - bought a - that was either - buying your books or else going to the pictures you see. You couldn't do - couldn't 
do the both.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Do you remember your mother and father reading, apart from looking at the newspaper?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
No, I don't think so, I don't think my mum used to do a lot of reading. Yes. You see, when I - right up until I was married there was no electric. 
There was oil lamps, you see. And - you can't read - you couldn't read by oil lamp. I mean I'm talking about my father reading the paper, as - that was the simple reason - that he used to read it - soon as he came home from work, so - I mean, it wasn't da
rk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did they ever read out aloud to you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Or as a family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No, no, no, never.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Do you remember ever having stories read to you as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No. No. That sort of - you see, those - sort of things weren't done then. N
ot like it is now. Exactly. You see, I mean, it was a case of - you going - when we went - when we went to school we used to have - come home and have our tea and we used to go out to play outside for about an hour, hour and a half. Well it was come in an
d
 wash and bed. You see? Well there was no question of - reading because as you say it was candlelight. And no lamps. I mean, oil lamps, you couldn't read by an oil lamp. You couldn't read by candlelight upstairs. So - it was - that was the cause of the tr
ouble I think.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Could your mother read?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
Oh yes, she learned. Oh yes, she read - could read and write and - and I mean - and my dad. My dad was a beautiful writer. He - he had a beautiful handwriting.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Do you ever remember a funeral in the family when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
Yes, my little brother. Now that was - I was dressed in a - a black coat - a - a black dress, with crepe all round the bottom. 'Cos that was the thing then. And I had a black hat with crepe round the - brim. And I was only 
very young, I wasn't very old. And I remember on - only had one - 'cos it was only a little coffin, you know, it was only a baby like that, and he only had one carriage. That was my mum and dad and my mum's sister. And that was - not a hearse, it was a - 
just an ordinary cab, and the coffin was inside. Not a hearse, not for that you see. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did you actually go to the church service?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No, not to the funeral, no, no. No, only my mum and dad and my aunt - went to the funeral. That's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Where did you actually wear this black?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
All the time. Yes. All the time, yes, for six months. Yes. Sometimes it was a year for - a big funeral, you know, grown up. They went in mourning for a year. But not now, they don't do that now do they. No. I rememb
er this black crepe. Clear as anything it was. Big - big band of it round the bottom of my frock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Do you remember if your little brother actually stayed at the house until he was buried?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Oh yes, yes, no they keep them - kept them at the house, u
ntil the day of the funeral. Then when we - when we - when the funeral was on I think we went to my grandma's, I'm not sure. Can't remember that. I know - I think we were just - when my - little brother died we were living down the bottom of - Artist Row.
 
Now I can't remember the date. The house - the number. But it was down the bottom. Not on the top there, where we lived, it was - it was - and - he died - down there with double pneumonia. Can't remember the name - the - the number because it was - all th
e houses are down now, I mean - all - they're all gone now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Do you remember any other funerals when you were a child?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No I don't think I do. Only my grandma's. But - I mean - I can't remember how old I was when she died. Of course I've known - a
nd my father - I mean - that year - that's about twelve no - about thirty years ago my father died. But not as a child, I can't remember any - more funerals. I can't remember ever seeing a funeral. When I was a child.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 There's only one cemetery on Portland isn't there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
Yes. YES. I remember seeing a Naval funeral. They used to come up round a zig-zag up to Naval tunes to the cemetery. Then - the officers had - big plumes and that and a big band, big funeral, I remember seeing that one.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 I heard something about Portland funerals being quite elaborate affairs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
Yes, well now - a typical Portland funeral - no women go to it. All men. That's typical Portland funeral. No - no women go to Portland funerals. Not the old ones, they - old Portland, only men.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Were you taken out visiting when you were a small child by your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Well - yes, only - only out to Preston to my - we used to go out there. And we'd go in - there was train then you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 You'd go on the train?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 From down
 the station. Yes. And then get off at - Malcom Regis. And then you used to have to walk from Malcom Regis to Preston, 'cos there was no buses. You might be lucky enough and - and meet a carrier - what they called a carrier man - going out - half way out,
 and get up then. Other than that you had to walk about three and a half miles. We used to go out there - well - used to make it Sundays. We'd go out there early Monday - Sunday mornings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Would you spend the whole day there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Spend the whole day and come back at night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 And you mentioned you got apples from them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
Yes. And plums and - redcurrants, blackcurrants, white currants, everything you could think about. Great big dumpling apples you know. Not little ones, great big ones like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Had they got a farm there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
No, just the orchard of - of fruit and that, no farm, just a long orchard with all the apple trees and plum trees and that. No farm. And my mother's father - my mother's father was the schoolmaster. And - he died and g
randma married again and she married a drunkard. And all the money that they had he - just drank away.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Were you taken out to visit neighbours or other people here on Portland?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No. No, 'cos you see all our friends were round about - where we liv
ed. I mean, we didn't have any friends on the top of the hill or anywhere like - oh - wait a minute, there used to be - my mum my dad's - aunt used to live up the - Alma - quarters here - Aunt Harriet, my mum's - my dad's aunt. Used to go up there sometim
es and see her. All went up together you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 All the family together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
Yes, yes. Mum and dad and - whatever children there were. I remember once - I didn't go out with my mum and dad, one Sunday afternoon, my - went out with one of my friends, a
nd I had a - a cinnamon - facecloth costume, well you know what that meant those days, there was - they was - that was expensive stuff you know, facecloth. It was like a - oh - I don't know whether you know what a facecloth is, smooth material. And it was
 
cinnamon. And I - I went into the larder, and I wanted something to eat. And I - tiptoed and I tipped - the rice to see what it was in the basin and it was a basin of gravy. And it went all down the front of me. Well - you could just imagine how I felt. S
o
 I - I got my skirt off, sponged it with cold water - hot water - warm water anyway, and me dress - and me coat 'cos it was a - a - what do you call it, and tight fitting here, 'cos I was very small you know. And - when my mum came in - I didn't know what
 
to do, didn't know whether to tell her what I'd done of what, so she said - changed you dress? Yes mummy. She looked at me a bit old fashioned. She thought, well, I know there's something wrong. I had to tell her. Gosh. She says, well - she said, I'll sen
d it and have it cleaned, and she said, that'll be your pocket money for a month. And I didn't get it you know. No pocket money. It'd cost more than that to have it cleaned then. Anyway I didn't get it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 How old were you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Oh - I must have bee
n about twelve or thirteen I should think. Yes. And I told her what I did, she said - how many times have I told you not to go to the food cupboard. If you want anything you wait until I get home. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 This was a rule was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Yes. Not allowed to
 go to the cupboard. No. Couldn't help - couldn't help yourself. Well she said, as - as - as I say now, you never know what you've got in the cupboard do you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did your mother go shopping into Weymouth at all and take you with her?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 She - no - no
, she didn't do a lot of shopping in Weymouth because there was no advantage. Because - you could get the things as cheap in Portland as you could in Weymouth.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did she take you shopping here then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Sometimes. It all depends where she went. I mean \endash  Newman\rquote s we used to shop - shop at Newman\rquote 
s. You know where the shop is shut down now by the bus stop. That was our store, we used to go up there, she used to take us up there sometimes. Saturday - Christmas time - we always went up with her. Because we
 used to pay in the Christmas club, and they used - used to open 'til ten o'clock at night. And we used to go up and get all our Christmas stuff. You know. It was fun then. We used to see what she had. Yes. Yes, but you could get an awful lot for the mone
y
 you paid in then. I mean you could - could get your - your oranges and your apples and - and your nuts for - next to nothing. I mean, it wasn't a question of - what - what were they, about three and eight or four - four shillings a pound. You could go an
d get a whole bagful of nuts for about two shillings. You see, it's a question of - food was cheaper.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Do you remember being taken out by your mother anywhere else?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No, not really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 You mentioned sometimes she took you for a walk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Just t
ake us for a walk down Castletown or somewhere like that. Round the gardens, round the gardens and - home. Sunday afternoons we used to go for a walk sometimes. She used to take us. I remember 'cos I was terrified of cows. I - I am now, I - I can't - I wo
n
't go in a field - where there's any cows. And we went up the Rerne Hill, and the cows were coming down for milking and - I wanted to go right up the top you know, out of the way of the cows. I remember holing on to my dad's hand as tight as I could. I wa
s so frightened. Come on, he said, they won't hurt you. And he guided me right in the edge you know, so as I shouldn't get near them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Do you remember all going out anywhere else together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No, not really. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 How about when the fair came?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 She - mum'd - let us go down the fair on our own in the afternoon. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 It's the fourth and fifth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Fifth - fifth and sixth of November. Of November. Always was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 You always went down in the afternoon?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Yes, in the afternoon, yes. T
hen - and sometimes then she'd say - well - we'll go down for an hour - in the evening to show you the lights and things like that, but you were never allowed to stay down there very late.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Would your father come with you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 What about money for the fair?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
Oh well we saved up our money. Weeks and weeks and weeks before that. Of course, as you say, I mean - you - you could down and you could go - go into a - the - trinket, you know, buy beads and things like that. You'd ge
t any amount of stuff for six pence then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Was there a lot of stuff at the fair that you couldn't buy normally then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 What - what do you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did you save your money and go and buy special things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Oh no, no, we - oh no, no, no, we just
 - just saved up our money just to have rides and buy trinkets or whatever we wanted to. That was our money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did your parents buy anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Well they used to come down and - sometimes they did buy anything like - their crokery or anything like t
hat, down there you know. YES? BUT at one time the fair used to be at Fortunes Well, years - not - I can't remember it but they say - it started at Fortunes Well, right down Fortunes Wells, right up by the - what you call it - the - by the rails there, th
e Britannia. It used to - it'd be up there, but I can't remember those times, I can remember - it being down - were it always is now but - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Was it bigger then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Oh yes, much bigger, yes. Much bigger.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 What sort of extra things do you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
Well, there was - confetti and - and - and things that - teasers and things like that they used to buy and then - flick 'em round you know and torment people and that. That's what they used to do. But there's nothing like that now. We used to ha
ve - just the - the round about and the swings and things like that, but none of these aeroplane things were in, they didn't have anything like that. Just swings and - and horse - you know, those - ordinary things that they've got now. No bingo or anythin
g
 like that. No - plenty - all - all hoop-la, of course there was hoop-la. There were plenty of cheap - cheap jacks, selling different things and that. Rifle ranges, that was all the - the - those, but not - no - the - cars, you know. Bumpers. Nothing like
 that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Somebody said there was prize boxing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Oh yes, well they - they used to - all - always had boxing down there. Always.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 It's not still there is it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Yes, you - yes. Oh yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Would your parents have gone down later on in the evening at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
Not on their own. No. I don't think they were interested that much you know. It was mostly for the children. They used to get - their free ride every time like they do now you know. The first - first day that they get a free ride, w
e always got that just the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Was there anything else like that that happened on Portland you remember you used to go to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No, I don't think so. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 What about Bank Holidays, did you do anything particular?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Well - I can remember - o
n - I wasn't very old, I remember - I went to Weymouth - browsing around you know, just - snooping round, doing nothing special. I - I was about fourteen then but I wasn't allowed - before that, I wasn't allowed to go out - to Weymouth or anywhere like th
at. We used to go out Littlesea - out picnicking and - bathing and that out there you know, at the Ferrbybridge up by Cosway there. We used to go out there a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Would this be with your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Yes, they'd come - mum, not my dad. My - My - my d
ad used to go over to his father's. But - when I was about - eight - nine, somewhere like that - during the summer holidays I used to spend all day on a beach, down there. Chadwell Beach, yes. I used to take my - I used to - have my breakfast, I used to t
ake my dinner - and - and my tea. And I used to go off about half past nine, ten o'clock, stay down there until nine o'clock at night, all day, playing. Bathing and playing shops and - you know, and - messing around. All day. Not come home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Would this be with friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
YES? Well all the children were down there, you know, I mean it was a general thing you know, everybody was down there, you know everybody. And - also - if the weather was - all right you see, you could guarantee the weather then. Yo
u could - you could go down there without a coat, just a frock. No stockings, just sandals. And stay down there all day. And never a shower of rain, boiling hot.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 This was when you were about eight or nine?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 There was no problem because the seas' quite dangerous isn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
Oh, yes, well we knew it you see, I mean - yes. But you know I've been fishing with a bit of cotton and a - bit of string and a pin. Bent pin and a - and a winkel - a limpet off the rocks.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Do you remember catching anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did you ever go away on a holiday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
No. Only to Preston, my mum - with my mum's sister. I was out there for a forthnight that's all. Well you couldn't do it you see 'cos there was no money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Was that when your mother was ill or something?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No. Just for summer holidays, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 That was just on one occasion?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 I should go nearly every year for about a week or a fortnight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did you have cousins about the same age there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Yes, I'd got a - I had a
 cousin, he was - he joined - later joined the Navy - at Greenwich school but - I used to - torment him you know, I mean I was a real beast to him. Well I remember once - he had a bike. And I let the tyre down. And - when he went to ride it he - he k}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid212699\charrsid16449734 new he - he'd pum}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 ped it up ready to go out and I was away in the cornfields.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 How old were you when you went on your own to Preston?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Oh I - I was about - eight, nine, ten, you know, like - I mean my mum used to take me and fetch me you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did you go on your own or did you have brothers and sisters with you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
No, I went on my own. She was - I stayed out there on my own but - I remember the first - time I went out, about three days I wanted to be home with my mum. I cried and cried and cried, but I soon got over it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Do you remember anything else particularly that you used to do at Preston that you couldn't do here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 It was countryside I suppose?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Yes. Yes. Used to roam around you know. It was nice out there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 I suppose you went climbing trees and that sort of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
No, I didn't climb any trees because my auntie - she used to say, if anything happened to you when you were out here, she said, I should never forgive myself, you stay with - I remember once - so
mebody threw some - you know those jam stickers that they call, you; know, those - things that stick in your hair? I remember once somebody - one boy, he threw some at me and my auntie - my Auntie Daisy - had to do my hair. Oh and she did - she said, I am
 going to cut it all off, she said, getting in this state. I shall always remember that. And I said, I didn't do it Auntie, I said, Billy so and so did it, and she said - you keep away from Billy so and so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did the others go at other times then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No, no, it was only me, yes. Only me.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Were weekends different in those days, how did you spend Saturday when you weren't at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Well as I say in the mornings we had to clean either the knives and forks, then in the afternoon - pictures. Even
ing - bath. That was all there was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 When you were little this was the same?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 And Sundays you had to go to church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Church, yes, yes, three times a day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did your father go to church at all on Sundays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No, my father never 
went to church or chapel. My grandfather did. My father - my grandpa used to get really drunk Saturday, but he'd get up and go to church on - chapel on Sunday morning.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 This was your father's father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Yes. Yes. Yes. Bet hopelessly drunk Saturday 
and then he'd get up and he has his bowler hat on and his white shirt and - all starched and - and his black suit and that and off he'd toddle off to chapel.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 This was the chapel you used to go to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Yes. At Brackenbury.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did they have any Sunday school outings?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Oh yes, they used to go to Otway. Otway for a strawberry tea. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 How would you go, on the train?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 OH yes, yes. Train.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Train and then the bus, or did the train go through to Otway?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Go - train went to Weymouth for Dorchester way, you know, up that way - that way. Oh yes, we used to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did they have any other sort of social activities?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 We used to have a - a - sports, you know. We'd have a - what we used to call a bun fight. And - they used to have - tea
 and buns and cakes. And then they used to have races after that for - oh we might win a - some beads or a handbag or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Where did they hold this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 They used to have that down the Naval Canteen ground - the sports. Because - the
re was nowhere up here you see. Always used to go down there, have their - have their treat and - and go down there afterwards and do their - run their races.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Was there anything else organized by the church or chapel you used to go to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No, I don't think so, I think that was the annual thing you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 When you were older was there anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
No. No, that was an annual thing and - when I turned over to church - I don't think they used to do - they used to have Girls Friendly Society, had 
concerts and that organised you know in the church hall, in the parish hall. At different times, but - not very - not very often. Well they might - well they might put on a concert one year and then - perhaps a couple of years afterwards put on another on
e, that sort of thing you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did you belong to the choir.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did the church or chapel run a temperance club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did you say grace at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No, no, we were never - you know - wasn't - not like that you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Were you taught to say prayers at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Oh yes. We'd say our prayers at night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did your mother hear them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No, she wasn't there, but she used to say, you say prayers? And I say, yes, whether we did or not.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did you have family prayers at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
No, no. The school that I - I - went to now are converted into police houses. St John's school. By the bus stop. That was St - used to be St Johns school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 So it was a church school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Yes, St John's - school, yes, church school that I went to when I was - well I started there. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 What was Brackenbury then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 The same, Wesleyan chapel school. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Yet you went to the Wesley chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 I went to Wesleyan chapel when I was tiny. Not to school, because it wasn't - I w
ent to St Johns church school because - I - I don't think - I can't ever remember - Brackenbury having a school there for tiny tots - when I was young. Because I can't remember anyone of our family or anyone - younger than me going to - up there. Because 
you see, I mean there was - Iris -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did you have any lessons with anybody else before then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No, no. We - went straight to school. At five years, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 What time in the morning did school start?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Nine. Nine o'clock. Home at twelve, until 
half past one and - home at four. And I didn't go to any - I didn't go to any other school but that one. Right the way through.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 From five?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Until I went to work at fourteen, yes, right through.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did you start afternoon school as well at the same time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Oh - oh yes, all day, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did you walk to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Oh yes. Yes. It was only just from - well - down the road there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 And you had an older brother and sister to go with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Yes. Yes, well I mean, more or less we went o
n our - you know, I mean I it was just a case of coming across the road and walking up the road, that was all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Was it a big school, it must have been a very big school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Yes, well there was - yes. Well yes, because there was the - there was the i
nfants class, then - then there was the next one up and then there was the separate school for the - boys and - I don't think the girls - I think the - the big class was for boys only. I don't think there was mixed up there, not for the big class, I think
 
it was only boys. But - like from say five 'til seven - you were in one - classroom. And then you went - to - from five to - from seven to about nine, right into another classroom. And then from nine 'til fourteen you went into the governess' room, the go
verness used to take us - from nine 'til fourteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Why was she called the governess?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
Well because - she was head one you see. I mean it wasn't a - it's not head teacher, well, she was head teacher but - it was termed - they were termed governesses then. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Governesses was a termed used for private tutors at home as well wasn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
Yes. Oh no, but she was - she was our governess. Now - it's - head teachers now. See, the term's head teachers but then - she was - governess.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Just a change of usage of the term?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 That's right, yes. It was the same principle, same thing, same kind of thing you know I mean - it's - it's equivalent to a head teacher.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 What did you think of school when you started?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Well, I - I liked it at fi
rst. And then - a Mrs Young - she was the head teacher for the - infants. And - Mr Young was the headmaster for the - bigger boys, older boys. Well now Mrs Young, she was the type of person - a nosey woman. I used to think she was ever so nosey. She wante
d
 to know all your - family history, you know, sort of - inquisitive. I - I didn't like her very much, but I used to like my other - I used to like the infant teacher, Mrs - Miss Flynn. She was nice. And - then of course there was - the other teacher, Miss
 
Durwall and Miss - oh I can't remember her name now but - they were nice, they were - as I got older - like in between times from Mrs - from Miss Flynn going into Mrs Young's, I didn't like Mrs Young. But when I came out of Mrs Young's class and went into
 Miss Christy, the head governess, I was all right. You see, it was just that little span - going through - I suppose it was that - I didn't like the teacher, that's all there was to it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Were you the only one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Oh no, I - I think - there were quit
e a few you know that - thought on the same lines as I did but of course - I mean we couldn't go home and say, oh Mrs - Mrs Young is ever so nosey mum. Couldn't say that because - she'd say, you go to school to be taught and you mustn't - you know -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Was she like it with everybody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Oh I should - I think so, she - no, I - no, I think she was - it was in general you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did the teachers emphasise certain things as important in life, such as manners?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Well no, I don't think they did, not 
- not as - not as much as they do now. I mean - you were sent to school to be taught. And - and that's all they did. I mean they didn't - they didn't - not like they do now, I mean, this - man that's just been killed, Mr Parry, he was an English teacher, 
and he's also elocution, and he also used to inspect their nails and their hair, you know, and they didn't do any of that when we were tiny.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did they emphasise punctuality?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Oh yes. Well -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Or tidiness?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Tidiness and punctuality, yes, if
 you were late, they wanted - they wanted to know why. And of course if - as - as today, if you stay away you had to give a reason why. You know, like if the children were - don't go to school - like today, well then tomorrow they have to take a note to s
a
y why they weren't there. Well we - that was just the same then, only we didn't take notes, we just had to say why - we didn't - and if there - if there was an epidemic like measles or anything like that and - and you had measles, or had measles in the ho
u
se, then you had to stay home. You couldn't go - I mean suppose my brother had measles, I couldn't go to school until he was better. You see? Yes, the quarantine. But they're not quite so bad now. They don't worry about you see, because there's so many an
tibiotics that can - sort of whip it up quick, that there isn't all that long drawn out -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 But was learning to be tidy and punctual part of your school curriculum?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Oh yes, you had to - you had to - be tidy, you had to be there on time. And also, y
ou were told if your hair was untidy or anything like that. You were very much that way, the same as they are now. But you see now - then another thing - at the school we were taught knitting - our own stockings. Well they're not taught that now. You see 
-
 I used to make my own long black stockings at school. And I was taught how to turn a heel and - how - you know, and the - the amount of wool it took for each stocking and that, you know, it was sort of - but they don't do that now. They do needlework, ju
st the same. We did needlework. But I don't - I don't think they have a knitting class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did the teachers bother at all about the way the children spoke?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Well no, no, I don't think - not so much as they - I mean - of course - elocution wasn't thought of then was it really, not individually.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did you have to ask for things in a certain way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
Oh yes. Oh yes, if you - if you - went to - supposing you wanted something from - the headmistress or governess or whoever she is and you went up and s
ay, I want so and so, and she will say, I don't think that was a nice way to speak. You - you say may I have, you see. That is the correct - may I have so and so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Is that the way she would have approached it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 She would have approached it, yes. A
nd another thing is - she was very much - I told you once, and the next time you'll get punished. Very strict on that way. I remember once - she said to me - Evelyn Gale, if I catch you speaking again you'll come out the front. And she hadn't got the word
s
 out of her mouth and I turned round and spoke to Ethel Elliot. She said, what did I tell you, out you come. See, just like that, very strict, still very strict. And I think they are strict now, as regards discipline in the school, so that - that doesn't 
alter very much.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 You mean you had to go and stand at the front of the class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Well I had to hold slates over my head. Six slates like this. For a certain period and - if your arms went down she'd say, hold them up.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 This was the punishment?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Punishment. Yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did they use a cane?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Not very often. Not very often.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Was there any other way of punishing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Punishment? Stopped from play, weren't allowed to go out to play. Do - sums or essay or something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did you have playtime the same as they do now?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
Oh yes. About - eleven o'clock I suppose a bell would go and you had your drill and then you'd get - ten minutes, quarter of an hour and in you'd go again. And if it was raining - you still had to go out, put your c
oat on. If - unless of course it was pouring. And if it was drizzle it didn't hurt.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Were the boys punished in exactly the same way as the girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Oh the boys would get the cane.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Who was this given by?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 The headmaster.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did they have to go to him specially?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Specially, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did he do it in his room?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No, in front of the children, in front of the whole - other ones.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 He would bring the cane back to the classroom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Yes. There was a family under the hill - by the
 name of Page. And they were a rough family. And - she was - went out one day. Well Mrs Young as I told you - she had an occasion to - have one of her children out. And - I suppose - I don't know whether she was a - a sort of a motherly type or not but sh
e
 - turned her child up and smacked her behind, you see, and she had no pants on. So the girl went home and told her mother and it happened to be a washday. And Mrs Page come back with her sleeves all rolled up here and she wasn't very - very tidy you know
,
 she was - very untidy. Bang, bang on the door, oh she - Mrs Young came back, and she got her hold by up here, and pulled her towards her and she said, the next time you smack my child's behind I shall do the same to you. And she was expelled from the sch
o
ol, she wasn't allowed on school grounds after that. And one of her sons threw inkwell at the - headmaster. In the - you know, because he was chastising over something. You know, they were rough lot. And there weren't very many rough children there. Very 
very few.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 This family came from further down?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
From - under the hill, yes, in - down Mallams and that - but - I can always remember - you know, him - just throwing the inkwell at - well we used to call him Daddy Young - Daddy Young.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 It was a very friendly little school then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
Oh yes. Yes it was. No, because it was Daddy Young 'cos they used to have some fun with him you know. I mean, he - he was a very tall smart man, but - I think he used to - go in with the boys to a certain extent you 
know, go in their - go their way sort of - not be so disciplinarian that - over different things. But - of course he had to do his job and that's all there was about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did the teachers treat all the children the same do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Well, I - I 
think that - the children that - that they taught, I mean - now, you know as well as I do that in a class you get the bright, you get the modern - medium, and you get the very slow don't you. Well - I think that - the bright ones - were left to get on to 
t
heir own devices because they knew they could do their work. And then the schoolmaster or schoolmistress whoever she is, she used to take pains - in helping the ones that were a bit slow, if she found - that they were helping themselves. But if they were 
- weren't interested well then - she - just give them their work to do and they didn't do it and that's all there was about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 You mentioned there one or two rough children, did most of the children come from a similar type of home to yours or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
Yes, yes. There weren't very many, there might - might have been - well one or two - ruffians you know sort of - not exactly ruffians but - not brought up in a - sort of a - strict way or - they were allowed to do more or less what they liked at home a
nd - the parents weren't interested. And therefore it comes out in the children doesn't it. I mean it stands to reason if you - let your children do as they like at home - they think they can do as they like anywhere else.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Was there any particular part of Fortunes Well where this type of family lived?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
No. No, that - they were all - this - particular family was living - used to live down Mallams, down one of the side streets. But as I say, there weren't very many - rough children about.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Were there any children that you felt were different in any other way, you mentioned that your sister went in service up Ventnor Road?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Yes, well - now Ventnor Road children - now there was a girl - one girl lived down Mallams, Betty Beggs her name was, a
nd she was brilliant. There's no mistake about it, she was brilliant, I think she ended up - a headmistress. But she was in the same class as we were. But the teacher used to ask a question and before anybody else could answer she was there. Now she used 
t
o live down Mallams, I mean, there's no - there was no special place for them to live. It was just the fact that - that she was - you know - brilliant and - now there was another girl - Ruth - no, I can't - I can't remember her name but she was a - she wa
s
 - she was next down to the headmistress, the next senior. Now she used to take this girl - and give her extra lessons after - school. Because she thought she was going to be - you know, clever. And she went and got another job, after all that tutoring - 
s
he went and got a job right outside to what she was thought. After all that extra work, you know. There used to be - used to be about six girls that sat up on - our desks were like that, going along like that, and then there was a long form and there was 
s
ix girls and they were - the top girls, you know, top form and - they were - they were fairly clever. But - they were in the same class as what we were. I mean, there was no - not that distinction, they were clever and they were - they got decent jobs aft
erwards because they were - top girls you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did your parents show interest in your schoolwork?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Yes, well they - as - much as such - we used to - go home and - my mum used to say, what have you been doing today? You know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did she actually ask you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
Oh yes, what have you been doing today? And we used to say all what we'd been doing you know. And - and then when - we left school, well there was no other - you couldn't - there was no jobs about, all you had to do was to go into service. YES.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Do you remember your parents going up to the school at all to see the teacher}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid212699\charrsid16449734 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
No, I don't - there wasn't - there wasn't a - like there is now - families day. There was no - you know, like now you get open day don't you. Well there was no such a thing as that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did they ever go and inquire of the teachers how you were getting on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
No I don't think so, I think - were - just took, you know, sort of from us. I think my elder - my oldest brother, he left when he was thirteen. He passed his eleven plus but there was no secondary - there was a secondary school but you had to pay then. P}
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid212699\charrsid16449734 ay in the secondary school. Wey}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 mouth secondary school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 So when you'd finished at St Johns you could have gone into Weymouth?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 St Johns. Could have gone into Weymouth, but you had to pay. Pay for extra - education. Not like it is now.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did any of the children that were in your class go on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 I think - I think the - I think - two or three of them did go over to - what they - not - it was a gra
mmar school now isn't it? Well it was called the secondary school then. Well - several - I should think about - six or seven girls - left school and went over there for further education. But they were in a position to do it you see. I mean, one -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 What sort of families did they come from then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
Well, one was a - had the - shop down in Fortunes Well, selling - paint and wall paper and things like that. The other girl, Lilian, she - her father had her - outfitters shop. C}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid212699\charrsid16449734 e}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 cily Barnes, she was - a po
lice - her father - her father was a Sergeant in the police. So I mean they were all in a position to send the girls. I mean there was no such a thing - as it is now, grants. I mean - if you go - if you - now when - when Hazel came - Alec came back - when
 we came back from abroad and Alec went to grammar school, I got a grant for her clothing. You see? But there wasn't such a thing in those - no such a thing then. If you didn't have the money you couldn't go and that's all there was to it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Would you have liked to have stayed on longer at school if you'd had the opportunity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No. No, no. I had enough, I didn't want to stay on at school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did you ever go to any part time education after you left school at fourteen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Yes, I went to night school. Out at Cliff school. I went out there and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Was this when you finished school at fourteen?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
Fourteen, yes, after - oh yes, I was about sixteen I suppose, I went to night school for a term out there. Just - nothing - no commercial or anything
 like - just ordinary - as you did at school, you know, sums and essays and things like that. If you wanted to go in for commercial and that well then there were - you had to go to Weymouth for that. You see, this was a teacher, a Miss Wallace I think or 
Mrs Wallace came in from - Wyck every Monday or Tuesday for - from eight o'clock until - oh half past seven until nine I think. But you had to pay. Yes, I don't know how much it wasn't very much I don't think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did you decide to go yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Yes, 
I - I thought I would be very clever and go but - I - I suppose it helped me. Because - I mean when I went - when I went out, when I got married and went out I was able to - sort of stand on my own feet you know. And - sort of mix in with people and conve
rse with people. Where - if I hadn't gone - to night school - I don't say that I wouldn't have done it, but it would have been - wouldn't have been so easy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 How long did you do this for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Only just for a term. Like it's - you start - in October, a
nd it brings you up until - I don't know, February I suppose. Just a term like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did you pay for it yourself or did your parents pay for it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No, my mum paid for it, I didn't pay for it myself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 And it was your idea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did any of the rest of your family go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
No, they didn't want to go. My sister - my - Iris, the one - the next sister to me, she said that she was going, but then she - she dropped out, she didn't - no, she thought differently. So she wouldn't go. No, she w
as a cashier in the - in the butchers shop down there before she got married. Whitton the butcher. Yes, she was cashier down there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Do you have any regrets about your education?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Yes. I think that - if I'd known what I do now I should have paid m
ore attention and - and - I should have taken - I should like to have taken up English. You know, concentrated on - knowing English more. Because I think it's an asset. I - if you learn English - and - you get your - sort of - outlook on different things 
and that - you talk nicely. And if you've got a little bit of English and you can pronounce your words, you can get there.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 I've heard several people on Portland say this.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Yes. Elocution is one of the finest things out to get anywhere, did you kn
ow that? Now you get a - I don't know how - how you - how you find - Portland people, quarry people, how they talk. Yes. No, now you see, only they - they've got - we'll be going, you see. Don't know none of 'ee, ee, they baint none o' 'ee. That's the Por
t
land talk. But you - if you - now, we have some people come round from - from - up the North, Hull way, Leeds. And my brother is a proper scream when he starts and he'd say - yer, you baint none o' wee. And they say, well what you talking about Joe? Well 
- you don't belong to us. And he talks in real Portland dialect, and they thought it was wonderful. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did you call it Portland dialect?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Well - Portland talk, dialect I suppose, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did you talk like this in the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Oh no. 
No, no, we - we were - we weren't - come - didn't come in contact - the top hill people are the Portlanders you know. Under hill people, you don't find very many Underhill people that talk real Portland. And if you get a real people from Southwell - real 
P
ortland, you, and neither can I, understand what they're talking about. Now the - the - in the olden days - if anyone strange went up - well say - Channel - not Channel View, Avalanche Road, Southwell, Seethill all up round there, the old ladies used to -
 draw the curtain back, who be she, she baint nane o' we, you know. That's how they used to talk.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 But you don't remember this as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Down in under}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid212699\charrsid16449734 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 hill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Your regrets then are seem to be almost a difference in education between now and then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Do you have any regrets about the type of education you had then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Well - no, you see, the - the kind of education that we had then - was available to how they could teach. See, I mean - they taught -
 now you - you - you go to school now and their method of doing maths is different - entirely different. You see? I mean we were taught and we only know that. We couldn't go into a place now and say - well the children'd say, well, what on - what on earth
's that. You - you taught them how you -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Do you think that you benefited from attending school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
Oh yes, I think so. 'Cos there's lots of little things that you learn. Sticks. But the only thing is that - I wish I'd paid more attention - and got 
more knowledge of - everything, you know, sort of thing. I - I - I just - wasn't interested. All I went to school was did my work and home again and that's all there was to it. Now my brother see, I mean, he - he worked and - he was all right. My other br
o
ther - he - he - he was a telegram boy, he got a postman, he's coming out as an inspector. He's got thirteen a week - thirteen pound a week pension now, because he - worked and he studied. See? Well I didn't get the chance. See I didn't get the chance to 
s
tudy, because when I left school - I had to stay home, if I didn't go out to work, I mean, I was - out to work but at the same time I used to go home from work and at seventeen I was cooking a dinner for a - family. A whole family. My brother - the - my f
ather and my younger brothers and sisters. And it wasn't just - few potatoes, it was a great big }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid212699\charrsid16449734 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734  boiler}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid212699\charrsid16449734  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 ful}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid212699\charrsid16449734 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
 of potatoes. Cabbage.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 What had happened to your mother then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Was ill. She had asthma. She used to suffer with asthma terrible.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did she in fact get worse then at this stage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
Yes, but she was - she used to get these attacks of asthma. And if she had an attack of asthma she used to stop in bed. She couldn't breathe. It was no good her getting up and trying to do things, she was fa
r off better laying down or - or propped up, she couldn't lay down, propped up, resting, see?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did she get worse as you got older?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Oh yes, as - as we got older and older, yes. My - we were all called to her bedside once, we thought she was going 
to die. I can remember it distinctly, I was only about - eleven, ten or eleven, I suppose. And I remember saying, oh mummy don't die, don't die. And I can hear her now, oh I feel better now. I can hear her now, you know. But - apart from that I used to - 
o
f course I - I mean - I'm not going to say that I was an excellent cook but I did the best I could. And I used to stand at the bottom of the stairs, 'cos we had the stair door you know that latched don't you? And I used to say, what do I do now mum? And t
hat's how I learnt my cooking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 And you say your brother had the opportunity to study?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
Well, he - he was a different type - I mean I suppose really - he could - he must have had it there because he passed his eleven plus. And he was out of work fo
r so long, he couldn't get any work. He - for - four years he was out of work in that slump you know, 1926. And - but there was no question of - going into a office somewhere. You see?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 You said you enjoyed school, did the children have gangs at school or particular groups?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
No, I don't think so. I don't think that - I don't think we did really, I think we all - when we - you know, when you go out to play - out with other children, we just - played with - like a little - a few, I mean, all togethe
r and that, but - I never - we never had any gangs like they do now you know. You know, you get the - there's about six or seven girls, they all cling together, and of course as - as I say the education is different today as it was then. 'Cos I mean the g
irls - at Tophill school, senior school, they smoke and - you see, I mean to say, there - there's a different outlook on life. Altogether.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Do you remember any children that were left out of things at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No I don't think so. I think they were tr
eated very well altogether. I think they were - one - as I say, the brilliant ones - which is natural, I mean to say, if you've got a - you go to a class, you've got a class of children, and you've got a couple of brilliant ones that's going to make somet
hing of their lives you're going to help them, aren't you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 I mean more amongst yourselves rather than the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No, but I mean - you see - and - perhaps they were they were the little bit of outstanding ones but on the whole I think we all - 
mucked in together, I don't think there was any gangs or anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did all the children of your age group go to St Johns school or do you remember any children going off to any other school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No, all the children of my age group went.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Were there any children that went to private schools?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
No, I don't - no, I don't think so. No I don't think - there is one girl but she went to - I don't know what - I can't remember the name of - the private school that was under the hill, she went there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Was there a private school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Oh yes, yes. I can't remember the name now. Offhand.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid212699\charrsid16449734 Where about}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734  was the private school?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Down - down the bottom of - Fortunes Well. And - oh I can't remember that name now. And her name was Gwen Weills, we
ll she went to the private school, and then when she was about eight or nine she went to a Convent. 'Cos they had the - the money, they used to - you know where the - block of flats are opposite the - they're empty now, all those flats that are empty, the
 Wall, you know there the second}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid212699\charrsid16449734  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
hand market is don't you? Yes, well that used to be the Royal Hotel. And they - her mother used to keep that. So that I mean they were in a position to send her to the Convent. Dartmouth - Dartmouth - High School it was. Dar
tmouth High School under the hill.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did you mix with the girls that went there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
No, well there was only - one or two, I didn't know the others very well because - I suppose really - not - by going to the private school, you didn't sort of mix wit
h them very much. But Gwen Wills, she was - she went there and she - went to convent and eventually she got married, she lost her husband in the war. But she still - she - although she - she talks beautifully. I mean she had her education - she had her ed
ucation you see, and - she - still she'll stop and - speak to you now. I mean she didn't have that - didn't get that little bit of aloofness or - you know, snobbishness. That they usually get.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 So do you have any regrets about your education then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
I - I don't really, well I don't really - if - if the money had been there I could have got a better education but - there wasn't the money and there you are.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 In what ways do you think the education was different in that private school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 OH well
 you learnt - I suppose you - you had your elocution lessons, you had your - well it all comes in manners and things like that and - it - it's a different - tuition from private school and - and Convent than ordinary - day school. I mean I know that from 
A
nnette. My daughter. See? I mean every - I - I - I firmly believe in - in a Convent education. Because the - the nuns, they - they've got not outside attractions. They can teach the children. They - I mean they concentrate on their work, and their - inter
e
st is in their work. I mean none of them are the same, the teachers of today. Ordinary schools are not, but they've got no - the - the - the Convents and the nuns have got no outside attractions. You see? No, well - no, I mean you need not be, I mean I do
n
't - wasn't a Catholic you see. She went. And - Hazel - she went to - St - no - no, Hazel, Kim, my little granddaughter went to St Philomena, in Wyck for a little while. Now - she talks nicely. And the different - I mean, the ordinary schools, they teach 
t
hem manners but they don't teach them - what can I say - well, finishing off, yes, a polish. They don't teach them that. They teach them their manners, and they'll say, now - Miss Dart - she's retired schoolteacher - if a child passed her and say - didn't
 say, excuse me Miss Dart, she'd take 'em right back and she'd put them there and she'd say, and you walk past and you say, excuse me Miss Dart. You see? Well that's all right, but the - it's not the polish there.
