\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did your father take an interest in politics at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
Well - as you know, those days it was only Conservatives and Liberal. There was no Labour, you see. Well my father was a Liberal. And - he never used to go to meetings in as much as they've - got meetings, today, I mean, they've got -
 Conservative meetings different times, and that. Well - whether they had them at - my father never used to go. But when it came to voting time, he'd go and vote. And I suppose really in his own way he would - I don't know, I suppose he followed up - the 
Liberal parties and what they did and that. But he never con}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid9253336\charrsid16449734 v}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
ersed over - on it. All I know is that he went to vote on the voting day and he voted Liberal. That's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did he talk about it with your mother at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Oh I - I don't know, I don't th
ink - I don't think they were that much interested. In - the different parties or either - you know, they were - Liberal and other people were - friends was like conservatives, that's all there was to it, that's - I mean, not like it is now, I mean you - 
you see the council have got Liberal - Labour and Conservative. Well they never had - used to have that in the - in the councils.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 What do you remember about the councils then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Well - not very much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Was your father involved with this at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
No. No. All I know is that - all I can think of is - when my father - he finished Mr Patten and when he finished Patten's and - he worked on the council for a little while, then of course he was ill and died. He was - only worked there for about - I 
should think about eighteen months. Then he had this illness and died, but - that's all I can remember about -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did he take any interest in local politics as well as national ones?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No, he didn't, no he wasn't a political man at all. Just everyday you know, sort of -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Why do you think he held Liberal views?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
I don't know, I haven't the slightest idea. I suppose working class - again. 'Cos most working class people were - Liberals. As they are with Labour. I mean to say you must admit that 
- the Conservative people are the moneyed people. I mean, no, I mean you've got to face it haven't you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did your mother go and vote?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 I don't think she did. No I don't - I don't ever remember my mother going and voting.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Do you know what her views were at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did she agree with your father do you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
Oh I don't suppose she - we - she never - they never conversed about it and I think she must have agreed with him to a certain extent to the fact that - he was a Liberal and she was a Liberal and - all that it stood for.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
In some places at this time men felt that they risked losing their jobs or their houses if they voted differently from their employers, do you know if this sort of pressure occurred in Portland?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No, I don't think so. No. No. I've never heard of it. No. No, no. I don't think that ever occurred here.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did your father ever work for one of the political parties at an election?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Oh no, no, he only just worked for the council, you know, ordinar
y - carpentry work and that's all there was, he never worked for anyone else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did he go out and help with the election at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No, no. No - no, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did your father go to any clubs, you mentioned he went to a pub occasionally in the evening?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
Well, no, no, only - I think he - if he went where the - the New Star is now, it used to be the Prince of Wales, he used to go there for a drink occasionally, but he never used to drink an awful lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did he belong to any clubs at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Were there any clubs like this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
Well no, I - I don't know, I think that - if I can remember rightly, it - there was a - a club where the British Legion is now, it was - the Conservative club. Well we used to call it - now who was the Co
nservative - can't remember - Yarborough I think it was. Yarborough Hall we used to call it. Up the Yarborough Hall, that was where the British Legion is now. That's the only club I can think of.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 You say your father was Liberal anyway?
