\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 He would
n't go there, no. No. And there wasn't a - there wasn't another club anywhere. I mean there wasn't a working mans club like there is now. At the bottom of East Street. I mean you know it do you. Yes, well there wasn't that one there. Then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did he take part in any sports at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
When he was younger he used to be - play football. When they were married first. Of course before - long before I was born. But he - he used to play football quite a bit then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 For a Portland team?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Well I - I don't know whether it was Portland or Preston, I can't tell you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Do you remember him going to the races?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Or betting?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No, no, he never did anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did anybody from outside the home help your mother to look after the house or the family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Even when she was ill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did they neighbours come in at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 They might come in and - say, did you want anything up the shop, or anything like that, but never come in to do anything. No. And yet
, you know, at - at - not my house, not our house but - at different times you know - the - the neighbours - the people in Portland, they used to help one another quite a bit. It was a question of - taking a meal in or something like that. But not any mor
e, not now, that's finished.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Do - you remember this happening when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
Oh yes, I remember - no, I remember - my next door - our next door neighbour, Mrs Holly, she - if she wasn't - oh and Mrs Martin it was first, - if she wasn't ve
ry well my mum used to pop in and make a cup of tea for her. And also there used to be a woman down - lived down further to us - Hansell, Mrs Hansell. My mother went to see her once. And - made her a cup of tea and took it up to her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Were these older women or were these families the same as you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
Same as - same - they would be a same - on the same level as us, you know, same age as us. I mean there was - Mrs Hansell's daughter was the same age as me. At the time you know, that sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Were these the children you played with normally?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
I - in the High - in the - in King Street. Yes, you'll find that - the people of today don't run in and help a neighbour like they used to. They never think about it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Was there any other way that neighbours helped when your mother was ill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Well no, only just to go to the shop or anything, 'cos us girls were home you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did they help with the younger children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No. No. No, we - always did that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Do you remember what happened when your younger brothers and sisters were born, did anybody come in then to help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
No, I don't think so. Might have been a - a aunt or something like that, but I don't think anybody came in - I couldn't have - I wasn't very old you know. I mean how 
old is my sister, she's - she's ten years younger than me. I can remember when she was born, and I remember my aunt - my mum's sister coming over from Preston, helping. But no neighbours outside.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Do you remember your mother going to help anybody when there was a baby expected?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
No. My grandma used to. My mum's - my dad's mother, used to deliver babies. But she had to work with a doctor because she wasn't a certified midwife. See, but she used to go - I mean there was a - a young girl by the name o
f - Vesta Reed, and she lived - you know King Street, you know where May had this hairdressing shop, you know the shop - the houses opposite, up the steps? Well she used to live up there and when - of course Vesta was only sixteen when she had her baby, s
h
e wasn't married, and - and Mrs Reed said to grandma - Grandma Gail, will you come when - Vesta needs you? And she said, yes. Well then she came down - they sent down for her at twelve o'clock one night, and my father - grandpa kicked up such a fuss and h
e
 said, you're not going to go up there and nurse that - she said, that girlie, she said. She said, not married, she said and - he - but she said, now Jim, she said - I'm doing it and - that's all there is about it. And she stood her grounds and she went, 
and he didn't like it at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Was this a common attitude?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Oh - yes. Well I mean -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 What happened to that family then?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Well her mother - the baby was - born, and she married and American and went to America. She married the father and w
ent to America. And she was only sixteen. But she was a bad lot because - her mother used to lock her in. And - she - somehow or other she'd get out and they used to find her up the quarries here three or four o'clock in the morning. That was just one - y
ou know, outstanding thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 What did your parents think of this then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
Oh my mum never used to say much you know, 'cos she was - my mum was a - a good, you know, Christian woman you see she would never - talk about anybody and she would never down
 on anybody. She's say, oh well - they've got to pay for their wrongs and that's all there is to it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did your parents have friends at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 What - what do you mean? Well no, my mother was the type of woman that - was friendly with everybody and n
o special friends sort of thing you know. She never had people in her house. Gossiping or anything like that, but she was friendly with everybody. And my father was the same. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did they ever go to anybody's house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No I don't think so, I don't
 think mum used to go out anywhere, she used to go out to Preston to see her - own people and that, but she never used to visit - I can't ever remember going into anybody's house, sitting down and having a cup of tea. But they - they weren't that - kind o
f people, you know, I mean - she used to - if anyone came to see her, sort of - offhand you know, she'd say, oh come in and I'll make you a cup of tea. But it wasn't a habit. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did this go on much do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Oh I suppose it did in other peop
les houses and that but not with ours, we didn't - 'cos you see, my mum had the family round her. You see, she had us children and that and - she was always there and I suppose she never - it never entered her mind to - go out - visiting or - having peopl
e there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 I suppose on Portland everybody's so inter-related it's a case of relatives coming anyway?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
Yes, well you see my mother was a Preston woman, she wasn't a Portland woman. She was born in Weymouth really but she was a Preston woman and ther
efore - she wasn't a - married into the - any Portland people you see. But on the hill you don't know who you're talking to. I - I mean - you can be - I can be talking to somebody and say - oh so and so and so and so, they - they'll turn round and say, we
ll you don't you say that because that's my cousin. You see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Was it like this in Underhill as well?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No, not so much Underhill as on top to the hill. Very very little intermarriage on the - under the hill.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Were there a lot of people came into under}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5900723\charrsid16449734 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 hill from the rest of Dorset then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
Yes. Quite a lot. Wait a minute, a lot of people came in from Weymouth, married - wed Portland boys you know. But you'll very - very seldom find - now I was talking to someone waiting for the bus about - a c
ouple of months ago. And I was talking to her and - I thought to myself, well I don't know, you're talking a bit freely about - Gladys, that was my cousin, see. So I said, well - what do you know about Gladys? What do I know about - Yes. Then there - you 
see, there was a - a girl lived under the hill, she - she married a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5900723\charrsid16449734 - a Smith. Bert Smith, on - from}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
 the top of the hill. Well now she's gone back up top of the hill to live, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Many people divide society into different social classes or groups, 
in that time before 1918 did you think of some people as belonging to one group and some to another group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 What - in what way do you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Well which group would you put your family in? Would you say everybody was the same in under}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5900723\charrsid16449734 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 hill or were there different groups of people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
Well I think they were more or less the same, I don't think there was a - a lot of difference in them. You know you don't get the - you didn't get the snobbery there, I mean - you didn't get the - people who thought 
- themselves above everybody else, I think they were more or less on the level. I don't think there was a lot of - class distinction there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Were there some people who were considered more important then than others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Well I don't know, I don't th
ink there was. I don't think that - no, I don't think there was, the only thing is - the business people used to be - I suppose - considered their - self a little bit better than - the working class people, which is natural. I mean that is the only distin
ction, you do find a - I mean, now like the girls }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5900723\charrsid16449734 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734  Honey}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5900723\charrsid16449734 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
man that kept the shop - and that, well - she would mix - to a certain extent, but then she had her friends - in business as well sort of thing. I mean it wasn't a - a case - question of - distinct c
lass distinction there, it was just the fact that - they had a different outlook on life as regards - the company they kept, I mean if you - I mean to say now - if - my daughter - had plenty of money and - and she mixed in with somebody else with plenty o
f money - she wouldn't cut her friends short but then she would - keep with them because she could keep up with their level sort of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Were there activities then for the business people in the town, did they meet anywhere together?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Oh no. No, no, I don't think so, I don't think there was any - sort of social gatherings there amongst the people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Do you remember your parents showing respect to anybody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Touching their cap or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No, no, I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Or calling anybody sir or madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
No, no, I don't think so, I don't think they ever came in contact with anybody that - very much according to - you know, in that - sphere of life. No, I don't think so. Can't think of anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Were there any people who you considered not to be the same level, a lower level?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Oh no, no, I mean -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Your father was a skilled craftsman wasn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 My father was a skilled craftsman, yes. No, we never - we didn't - look on people, if - if they weren't - di
dn't have any - you know, sort of little - jobs or anything like that we never used to take much notice of them, they - everyday life and they - if they were there we'd speak to them and if they weren't - you know if they wanted to go their own way they d
id. But there was no - distinction there. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Were you taught to say sir or master or madam to anybody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
No I don't think I was. I don't think I - there wasn't any occasion. I mean, I - I've worked - when I was about - what - how old was I, about 
eighteen, nineteen, for the Clerk to the Council, a Mrs Coalnut. But I used to call her Mrs Coalnut and - and him Mr Coalnut. I never used to call her madam, or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 How about your sister who went into service?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No, she used to say
 Mrs Reed. Wouldn't call her madam or anything like that. We - it wasn't - it wasn't - an understood thing then you know. I mean to say it was just Mr and Mrs and that and no sir and madam. Not like it is now. I tell you on one occasion my sister - Marion
,
 she was - working for a Doctor Brody, you know the doctor's that just retired, and - her - she had to go - she had to wear uniform, cap and apron, and they used to entertain a lot and - but she had to announce the guests at the door, which what I call is
 
snobbery. Because they weren't in the position to do that. I mean she was only a - a staff sister at Dorchester hospital. But the - her position got the better of her you see and she - had - people announcing her guests at the door, but - but that to me i
s all wrong. I mean there was no need for it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did you have any contact with the Navy people from down Castletown at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Were they considered to be different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No, I don't think so. Even - I had a friend that was }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5900723\charrsid16449734 \endash }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734  house}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5900723\charrsid16449734 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 parlour}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5900723\charrsid16449734 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 ma
id to - Mrs Bordon Coombes, now - he was something to do with the - coaling - shipping and that down the dockyard, down at Castletown, and - Mrs Coombes, she was a - her people had the - pub down there. Now - even then - she - they had plenty of money and
 they were in the position to be able to be called madam. But they were never - she was never called - she never - wanted her - her maid - she called - had a house}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5900723\charrsid16449734 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 parlour}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5900723\charrsid16449734 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
maid and a cook, but it - it was always - Mrs Coombes, Mrs Gordon Coombes, it was nev
er madam or sir. Because it was the way I suppose, life was then. It's - if - now if Mrs Gordon Coombes had - with her title and her money, she would have a staff and she would - she would be madam and he would be sir. But not so then. You see?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 I've talked to some of the people in the villages there were people like the squire?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
Oh yes. Well that's different. Because - in the - in a village - I mean - the - the - the village people - are brought up in a very raw way. Very - sort of - not common wa
y, but a very very - primitive way. And therefore when the squire - when they go to the squire it is sir and madam. Not so much the madam. It's the sir. They don't say madam so much but it's the sir.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Do you remember this when you went to Preston?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
No. Because - no, because - I mean - all the squire and that, they were on a - on - more our - out landing you see, Preston - was only a small village. And they didn't have any - squires or anything like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 What about the clergymen then, did they mix in with everybody or did they keep themselves to themselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
Well - how - now - where St John's is now - when I was tiny - when I was small, I should be about six or seven, eight or nine, somewhere like that, there used to be a Doctor Ockley. No
w his daughters, and they were very very nice people, very nice they were, they were - very very kind to the people, to old people and anybody that was poor. But as the years went by and the other vicarage people came - he died and somebody else took over
,
 somebody else took over, well - as time went on so - the - according to the church, it was a job. You see? I mean - now at one time, Doctor Ottley, and I think - I can't remember who took - there was - Captain - Mr Wrierleys and Mr - Mr - oh I can't reme
m
ber their names now but at one time Doctor Ottley always used to visit the sick. But you - they don't do that now. No padre visits the sick in Portland. I know somebody who used to go to church regularly, Holy Communion in the morning regularly, Sunday mo
rnings and Sunday evenings. She's crippled up with arthritis and he's never been near the place. You see, I mean it's as different then as it was now as regards - the church life.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Do you remember the vicar coming to see your mother at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 NO. A
nd when my sister - my sister - Ida that died with cancer - now she was a big church worker, she used to do all the teas like - I help now. I don't - the other girl took over, you know. Well now she used to do all the teas, and she used to do everything f
or the church. And when she was lying dying - the vicar was in the house, in and out in ten minutes. I mean that is the difference you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 But you remember when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 He used to visit the sick, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did he associate socially with the business people or anybody particularly then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
No, I don't - I don't know about that. I mean - I can't remember - the people - you know, like the vicar and that mixing so much, not as much as I do now. Now it's a question of - well - I mean two 
people in Portland - are big church workers. I'm not going to say - that they - what they do but they - definitely give donations to the church. And if you give donations to the church, with our vicar we've got now - you're in. You see? No, that is a fact
. I mean, if you've got no money - I don't want to know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 How about your father and his relationship with his employer, Mr Patten, Mr Patten was up at Top Hill wasn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Yes. Yes. Oh he got on all right with him.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did your father consider himself to be the same sort of level as him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
Well I - I don't know about that. Now - my father used to - he could have robbed him over and over again as regards his pay. Now - my father used to - used to come to my father and he'll pay - he'll make out 
his time sheet and he'll say, well how much money do you want this week Jim? To my father. And my father could have said anything. Well I did so and so and so and so and so and so. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \ab\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 B}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 ut he wouldn't. He was very very straight, my dad. So he used to say what he - his pah was and that was that. No; organisation.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 How many people did Mr Patten employ then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Oh I don't know, I - I don't think - two or three, not a big lot, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did all the people in the working class then have the same standard of living do you think?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Yes. Oh well - I think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Or would you say there were different groups?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No, I think they were more or less the same. No, as - you know where the second}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid5900723\charrsid16449734  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 hand market is now don't you? Well that's where my father lear
nt his trade down there. Right at the back, I can see him now, you know, through a - children - I suppose he'd learnt his trade then but that's where he used to work, where a lot of his work was done. Right at the back in the carpenters shed there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Was that Mr Patten's workshop then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Mr Patten - yes, that was Mr Patten's workshop then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Were there any families then in Fortunes Well that had a lower standard of living?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No, I don't think so, I - I think they were more or less on the - same level.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Do you think everybody could have afforded meat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
Well you - you know what I mean, yes, but you must understand that - you could get a lot of meat for a shilling - then. I was only talking to someone on Friday about that. We went past th
e butchers shop and - and she was talking - about everything, and she says - well, she said, you could - go into the shop and get a shillings}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5900723\charrsid16449734  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 worth of bits. What we used to call the beef cuttings you know. And make a pie a great big - not a little one, a g
reat big pie like that you know. I mean everybody was doing the same 'cos everybody - was on the same level. And - and chicken or - things like that were luxuries. You - if you had a chicken you had - you were - having - had luxury then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 The rougher families then had the same sort of standard of living as you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
Yes, well - well - that - I should - I don't know, you see, but on the - the person I'm talking about, well one of the people that I'm talking about, a rough crowd, mother and father used t
o drink an awful lot. You see, and that's where it comes in. Used to go drinking and - there was no money for food and - and they lived a real drunkards life, you know, sort of home and everything. I mean the boys used to go out on the beach and pick up w
ood and chop - it and sell it round for beer money.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 For their parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 You see, that was - that's just one family.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Were you allowed to play with these children or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Well I mean, you - what could you do?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did your parents let you play with anybody?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
Well - no, well you see, it was a question of - when we went to school we were - they were at school and that and - the girl, one of the girls, a very nice girl and she's very nice - she grew up a very nice girl, I used to go aro
und with her. But she couldn't help her parents. I mean you've got to face it. I mean, I couldn't help what my - if my parents were like that I couldn't help it. So you - you couldn't down on anyone. And my mum - of course my mum - as I told you before, m
y mum was very strict. And - I wasn't allowed out - gallivanting the streets and that. So therefore it didn't make any difference when I played with them at school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did you ever go into their houses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 I went into - Page's house, the drunkards hous
e once. I went down to see where - Helen was, and - typical - drunkards house. Beer bottle on the table with a cand}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5900723\charrsid16449734 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
e in and - and - bread on the table and - you know. 'Course in - in later year - I suppose they see their folly and that so they - sort of -
 gave up the drink and - grew a sort of a little home together. But it was - many many years afterwards. I think by the time they - before they died, I'll sort of say about three or four years before they died they sort of come to their senses and lived a
 normal life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 What sort of job, did Mr Page have a job at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 I couldn't tell you what the did I'm sure. I've got an idea he was in the quarry.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Were there any families where the man wasn't working at all any of the time that you remember?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
No, I don't think - only that slump you know, that slump, 19 - when I - that was the - that was the - outstanding thing then. There were a lot of people out of work then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Was there a distinction then between craftsmen and people who did just labouring jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No, I don't think so, I don't they - they made all that distinction, it was just the fact that - my father was a skilled man and - and - 
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5900723\charrsid16449734 people like - you see the quarr}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 ymen were - were skilled, I mean you've got to - you had to - know how
 to cut stone and that, see that - there weren't very many people that - weren't skilled really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Were there just labouring jobs in the dockyard?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Oh yes, labouring jobs, yes. Get plenty of those there - in the dockyard.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did your father make any difference in this way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
No, no, no. No, my father was friendly with them all you know. He - he never went out with men, he never went out of an evening - like as - you know, like they do, the man'll go out and meet a friend and that, well he neve
r used to do that, you see, as I told you before he used to go to see his father and home again and that was his life.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Was it possible do you think at this time to move from one group to another, to move from being a labouring job up to a skilled job?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Well, no, you see, if you had a secure job you went to apprenticeship. From - from a - a boy. To get these skilled jobs.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Do you remember any family like this, that the father was just a labourer and he would afford to put his son into an apprenticeship?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
Well now - that - now - I know somebody that used to - pay for their son to go to - secondary school, for him - as a matter of fact it was three sons they had. And they skimped and skipped and paid for their sons to go to secondary school s
o that they could have a better - outlook on - you know, better job. But - I don't know - he - I think he was a - the father was in the quarry I think - or in the dockyard. I'm not sure where Mr Mackenzie was, in the dockyard I think. But what he did ther
e I couldn't say. But I do know that - they sent their three sons to Secondary school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did you have to go to secondary school before getting the chance of an apprenticeship?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No, no, no, not necessarily. No, but you see - if - now supposing - supp
osing you had a son - those days, and you wanted him to go in apprentice - you had to put a premium down. You see? Had to pay - for a start. Then he had to be - a five years apprenticeship. See?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 And you actually remember somebody who managed to do this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Oh yes. Yes. Oh yes, yes, apprenticeship, five years apprenticeship wherever he wanted to do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Was this unusual?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Well no - I suppose really - I - I think, on the whole that - anybody sort of - that had children - that wanted to look for 
- towards their future - would make an effort. But - very far and few - because the money wasn't there. You see - I mean - let's face it, we - I mean you - you - you get about - I mean four pound a week was a good wage. When you put a premium down of abou
t twenty pounds, it had to be found.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Do you remember anyone being described as a real gentleman or a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No, I don't - not - not in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Portland{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose} I don't think. No. No, well you see - the Miss Hockley's they were gentlefolk and that, Doctor Ott
ly's daughters and that. I never knew his wife, whether he - she - he died - she died years before - before - when I was very very tiny I don't know. But Miss Grace Ottley, she was - they were }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7880012\charrsid16449734 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734  they}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7880012\charrsid16449734 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
re very gentlefolk but I wouldn't say they were ladies. 
Now when I was in the Army - our Colonel, Colonel Thompson, now she was a lady. She was a lady born and bred, because - I mean to say - there was no - snobbishness there. She would come in - she came in to see me once and I was coughing and she sat on the
 
edge of the table - perched herself on the edge of the table while I was cooking and that and - and I said, you'll get the flour over you if you're not careful. She said, oh that' doesn't matter, she said, that'll soon come off. But you know, no snobbery 
there and yet she had a position, I mean, Colonel then was a good - you know - good rank. So you - I mean, they were about but not in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Portland{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
. 'Cos you couldn't call - Gaffer Sampson - up the Castle, he was no gentleman, far from it. He was a rogue. You see - he had a lot of -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 He was a quarry owner wasn't he?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
Yes. Now you see if he had a - a - people owed him any money - and they couldn't pay he'd take his - their land. You see? And that's how he got his land. 'Cos he had a lot of land in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname 
City}}Portland{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
. 'Course it's all gone now because - he died and - and his sons have - I think there's one son in the country somewhere, in a farm or something. But - Walter Sampson - who I worked for, his wife, second wife - he drank all the money away. He drank a bot
tle of gin a day. Well you can't do that on nothing - and keep a castle going like that and keeping - having a - the - the - the rates and - the upkeep of the castle was terrific. So eventually it had to be sold.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 When was it sold?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Oh - let me see -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 After Mr Sampson, the quarry owner, died was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
Oh yes, yes. Now I was - I've been retired eight years. Now let me see. Add fourteen on to that. And - wait a minute - and - yes - about twenty-six years ago. I was up; there. And - it was whe
n - when the Labour government came in. When a Labour government was in, because - he said - if the Labour government got - if the Labour government gets in, he said, we're finished. We'll have to sell out. And that's what happened.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did you ever go up to the castle when you were a young girl?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
Oh no, no. I had never been inside the castle until I worked there. Oh - oh I used to - they had a - the - the - the - Queen Mary and King George, they had their coronation - fete up there. Used to have a garden fetes up there a lot.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did you go up there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Yes, well I remember them because I had - I remembered getting my coronation mug. I've still got it. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Was there anybody else, like him, a quarry owner, living up there?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Oh I suppose - I don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Were they thought of as a different level, different group?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
Well they - you see - the working class - the quarrymen - used to - look up to Mr - the old gent. Old gaffer they used to call him, old Gaffer Sampson. Yes. Yes, well n
ow - they used to look up to him as regards their boss. You see. And what he did his private life was nothing to do with anyone else, but they used to respect him. And inside the - inside the - }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7880012\charrsid16449734 Pennsylvania}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734  Castle there's a little cottage called Woodbine C
ottage, and - Mr and Mrs Pullman used to live there, well he was the - used to tend to - the cows and things like that, odd job man you know. Used to - he was the - at one time he was the - cab driver for - Gaffer Sampson. Oh they've been dead years now. 
Funny little fellow he was too. Used to come in his white coat you know. And we used to - and the parlour maid and the - I was sort of a - I used to do all the heavy work up there, and - then there was the nursemaid and the parlour}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7880012\charrsid16449734 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 maid and that, we got him
 on the table once, was going to operate on him. He had his white coat on and he said - well you don't - we don't - you don't operate, we'll operate today.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 How old were you when you went to work up there then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Well }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7880012\charrsid16449734 - I was - about - well - I'm six}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 ty - I shall be sixty-eight next month, and I - I was on the home help fourteen and a half years, and I've been retired. And I was up there before then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 You mentioned business people apart from the ordinary working class people, and Mr and Mrs Young the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Yes. Now they were very aloof, they were very - cut off. They didn't mix. Not the Young's, Mrs Young and them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 In what way was their household different?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Well they - they used to have the schoolhouse. There was a schoolhouse
 then there. And - but they - they never used to - only mix perhaps with the teachers and that, but they never used to mix - never used to see them mixing up with - out - outsiders at all, you know, just - with the teachers and the - people of their own -
 level, you know, teaching and that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Were there any other people who had maids for instance or servants?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No, I don't think so. I can always - remember the castle. And the doctor. Doctor had a - a cook/housekeeper I suppose. Doctor Howard.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Who were the people who your sister went to work for then?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
Well she was only a - a - a Mrs Reed, her husband was a Captain Reed, she was a widow. It wasn't anyone - I mean, it was only just - she had a daughter, a schoolteacher and a daughter in the C
ivil Service. But they were nobody really. I mean you couldn't say they were gentry or anything like that. But the - the people, I mean, it was only the doctor. The doctor had a - housekeeper, a cook housekeeper, Doctor Howard and - but even Doctor Brody 
and - and - they had a housemaid and that but - I mean - nothing very special, I mean, just to do the - answer the door, answer the phone and - do the work and that and get the meals, that's all, I mean it wasn't a - question of having a house}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7880012\charrsid16449734 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 parlour}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7880012\charrsid16449734 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 maid 
and a cook and a - and things like that, not like the gentry do. In the country they get under housemaid, they get a cook, they get a house - head housemaid, they get the parlour maid, they get the nursemaid or whatever - they need a nursery, they get the
 butler, they get the boot}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7880012\charrsid16449734 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 boy don't they. You see, I mean - you don't get any of theat in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname 
place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Portland{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} at all, I've never known it anywhere.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Do you remember seeing a policeman around where you lived as a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Oh policeman. Ours used to be a fellow
 by the name of - policeman by the name of Varney, and a - he was a little short stocky bloke, and we used to torment the life out of him. Used to say to him - how many coppers make a bobby. And run like anything, he couldn't run after us you know. And th
ere used to be a very tall - policeman - by the name of Samways. So Mr Bardy used to say, I'll tell Samways he'll make thee - he'll walk thee down one. Yes. Policemen always around though. Yes, you - plenty of policemen then. But you don't see one now.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did your mother ever say to you I'll call a policeman, if you were naughty?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
No. Never said - and she never said there's a bogey man or anything like that. She never believed in it. 'Cos she doesn't think it's - it was right for to teach children tha
t because it made them frightened. Well she used to - she never had any cause for that she'd say, all right - I won't speak to you again, you know what was going to happen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 How do you think the police treated the people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Oh very nice. Very good. YES? VERY good. Very helpful if you need them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did you see anything of your landlord, the people who owned your house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Well - they used to live in the next street to us. And their name was Couch. And they used to dome for the rent every - Satur
day morning, that's all we used to see of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Were they a family similar to yours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Hae a little shop, no, they had a little general shop.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Was he a good landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Oh yes. I suppose as landlords go, I don't know, wouldn't - wouldn't h
ave anything done as per usual you know, wouldn't spend the money. But - I suppose it was all right, I don't know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 When your father was out of work did you ever get any help from the Guardians or the parish?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No. No, no, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did this happen on {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Portland{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 at all do you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
Oh no, you - if - if you were really destitute, I mean my father was the type of man, if he was out of work - well if - if anybody said, well Mr Gail, I've got a little job for you to do - will you do it? Well, it use
d to bring in a couple of shillings. You see, and as I told you before - you could get a lot for a shilling. So I supposing he - he; won - he - he worked and got ten shillings, well that was a big help because the rent wasn't very much, I don't know how m
u
ch the rent was, I can't tell you. But - now if you get out of work you get some people that - couldn't get a job, and - they used to go to the - to a place in a hall somewhere and they used to get what they called the parish. It's like a Social Security 
now. But it was called the Parish then. And used to get about three or four bob there. Didn't get very much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Do you remember any family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 NO, I can't - I can't think offhand of any family - that had the p}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7880012\charrsid16449734 a}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 rish at the time, I can't really think, bu
t - now when my father was out of work - and - when - when my brother was out of work and my father was working my father had to keep him. He never had any help at all. Clothing and everything. 'Cos they didn't get - there was no - dole. And - I mean, he 
-
 he couldn't go on the parish because - if he went on the parish they so oh well, if you've got so and so you can sell it. The means test they used to call it. And they'd say, oh if you've got a wireless you must sell it. And get the money. That's the sor
t of thing they used to do. Wasn't allowed any luxuries in that respect.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 What did people feel about the parish then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Well they thought it was degrading. to have to go to the parish.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did people in fact go there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Well they had to sometim
es some of them. But I can't think of any family, but they - I - I suppose there must have been families there. And where the - where the - if - now supposing - an old - any old couple and - one had died - and the other one couldn't keep the house going, 
w
ell you know where Portway hospital is don't you, that used to be the work house. And they'd have to go into the work house. And - that was the bare minimum then. Just as - poor food and al - a old bed and that, best they could do. And that's where Portwa
y got it's hospital - it's name from.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 It was Portway work house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No. No. You see - Portway got its name from - because it was - old age - it was a - workhouse for {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Portland{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose} and {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Weymouth{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. So when they had a hospital it was Portwey.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Do you remember anybody having to go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
No, I don't - I don't know, now I won't - wont' be sure but - I've got an idea there was - a very very distant - relative of ours, by the name of George Parker, now - I can vaguely remember - this George Parker. And I can'
t remember - how - where the relationship came in, it was so distant, and I think he ended up in the work house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did you ever go there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 I went once - I went once - now what did I go there for? I went there once to see a very very old lady, and -
 it was pathetic. Whitewashed walls. Iron beds. Oh it was - typical workhouse. And I wasn't very - it was - an impressive age I suppose you know, I must have been about ten or eleven, and my mother took us to see somebody. Or took - we went in, I don't kn
o
w who it was, I can't - 'cos it was no relative of ours. But it must have been somebody that my mother - knew or something. And - I remember seeing these - oh it was terrible, I thought it was an awful place. Whitwashed walls and iron beds and - oh - terr
ible.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 When there was somebody in the district who the people disapproved of strongly was there any special way in which they showed it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No, I don't think there was, I don't think they would - if any undesirable were - came in or anything like tha
t - I don't think they were - sort of pushed away or - or put aside but - if they - if there was anyone came and - and - nobody liked them they soon made - off on their own, sort of thing you know, find that they weren't wanted and - go away. I don't thin
k there was any - sort of - unpleasantness or anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Do you remember anyone being made to leave by rough music?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No, no. No. What, being a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7880012\charrsid16449734 nuisance}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734  do you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 In some places people would get together with tin cans and things and bang them outside the door of the people they disapproved of?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
Oh no, no, no. No, no. No, I don't think - I don't think ever anything like that ever happened here. There used to be somebody coming - of course - they - they don't see that now, people used - me
n, old people, down and outs used to come round singing. Come round singing and - for coppers, did you know that. They used to come round the streets and sing. And get a copper here and there. Well I have seen that done.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 When you were a child, when you were young?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 What would your mother do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Just give 'em a copper, when she had any to spare and - they'd go - thank you, and off they go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did she make you go in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Oh we - we weren't - they were - I mean, they would
 be out singing out in the street and she'd send one of us out with a copper or something like that and - come back again, we weren't allowed to stand and listen or anything like that. We never knew who they were you see. I mean, they might be genuine and
 they might - might not be. 'Cos when I - since I've been home, I came home - from {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}South Africa{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 in 1946, well - Hazel was what, five, five and a half. And she couldn't have been any - any more than about - seven, six and a half, seven, and - I went out some
where - oh, I went over to the British Legion club to a meeting, and - she was - she went to a concert, a Primitive, you know where the Primitive chapel is, you know where the cake shop is down the - bottom of the hill, you know the little chapel there. S
he went to a concer}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7880012\charrsid16449734 t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
 there in the evening, you know, a concert and social night, and - she came out a big earlier than - she should have done, you see. Well our house in Artist Row is the top -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did you do any part time jobs before you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
NO. No, I didn't do any work at all until I left school but I - when I was fourteen I went to work at this house where my sister worked. And - I went from {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 19}}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}}seven o'clock{\*\xmlclose} in the morning 'til six at night, for half a crown a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 What were your duties, what did you have to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Was your sister still there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
No, she'd gone, she'd - I don't know where she went, she'd left and - I don't know what happened there. I know she left and I took over her job. Well my sister was there f
or eight years. And this old lady was a tartar. I was only fourteen you know. And no sooner I'd finished one job and she had another one lined up, and this went on all day long. And she used to let in - officers, you know, let her rooms to officers, to - 
she had a Captain Porter there. And I had to scrub bare}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7880012\charrsid16449734 -boards. And you know Venetian}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
 blinds I had to wash them, dry them, and polish them with Min cream, every lath, in in two big bay windows. Well - this went on, then I had to do the washing. I washed up 
all the dishes and - at night time - you know those little tiny lamps with - white globes, you know, them little tiny - she'd have one of those in the - in the scullery, that's all I had the light to wash up.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 So it was from {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 19}}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}}seven o'clock{\*\xmlclose} in the morning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Until six at night.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did you have any particular routine of things that you had to do when you first got there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No, I just had to wash up the breakfast things and help her make the beds. And then there was a general cleaning up. The bed
rooms and the downstairs, the front room and the front - room, the middle room, the kitchen. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Were you the only person employed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Girl, yes. Yes. Yes. Anyway -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Would she do anything herself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Only just help me make the beds, that's
 all. She used to do the cooking, you know, the main cooking and that. Anyway - I stuck there, I went home one day and I said, I'm not going back to Mrs Reed's any more. And my mother was - oh she was furious - she said - 'cos you see, the reason why my s
i
ster stayed there so long was - when my father was out of work she was very kind in sending - soups and - and - you know, bits down for us kids. Well I mean, I - I - quite agree she was very very kind and that, but she wasn't going to work me to death for
 it. And I stuck my grounds and I wouldn't go back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 So you did two years there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
I didn't do two - two years, I never did a year. No. No. I didn't do a year. I didn't do six months even. I think I was about four months up there I think. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 What did your mother say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
She was furious. She said, Mrs Reed was very good. I said, I can't help that, I'm very very sorry mummy, but, I said, I am not going up there, I'm - and I said, and I told her you know. And she said, I had no idea - and my s
ister had stuck it for eight years. She was too frightened to say anything. But I was different. I wasn't going to be sat on. And then - I went from there -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did she give you good meals?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 We were spring cleaning. Scrubbing boards and that and I ha
d boiled rice and jam, I had a little tiny bit of meat like that, and - boiled potatoe}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7880012\charrsid16449734 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
, no pickles or anything, and boiled rice and jam for afterwards. And I thought to myself, well I'm not working on that. Half a crown a week. Yes, I stuck that for about
 four months. Well then, I went from there - and worked as a - in a house in a china shop at - down the bottom of High Street, is now a - - - a solicitors office now, but it was a china shop at the time. Then I went from there down to corner.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 How long did you do in the china shop then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 About two years I suppose. I was a telephone girl -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Were you just serving in the shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No, housework. Yes, not in the shop, no. I was a telegram girl during the - well in 1920.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did you go to do the
 telegram job from the china shop, you'd been four months in service then two years with the people at the china shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname country-region}}China{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 shop, see that brought me up to sixteen didn't it. And - then I think - I was a telegram girl then, no - after that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 From the age of sixteen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
Sixteen. No, I couldn't have been because - I was a telegram during the - 1920 because - I took a telegram home - when the Proviso came ashore, down on the beach, a - a Russian ship - it was. And it came right inshore you know. 
It wasn't just - it came right in shore and I remember taking the telegram, so I must have been - I must have - worked between - Coalnut - I was telegram girl then. Eighteen. 1920. Yes. I must have been a telegram girl between the time I left - left - you
 know, the china shop, and then I worked at - for Coalnuts and I think I was married from Coalnuts, I left to get married there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 What was your job at Coalnuts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Housework. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Why did you go to be a telegram girl?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Well - waiting for th
e boys to come back from the war. This was the 1914/18 war. See, I suppose I must have been about nineteen I suppose. Between nine - nineteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did you have to go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No, volunteered. Volunteered, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Where were you based?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Oh at Portland
 Post Office. I used to do - one week from nine 'til - four, in the main Post Office. Down the Castletown we used to go from {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 11}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname 
Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 30}}}half past eleven{\*\xmlclose} 'til four. And then - down the main - down the Castletown again from one to - like shift round from one 'til four.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 You did shift work then between the two places?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Two places, yes, Castletown and - and Fortunes Well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did you just have to take the telegrams that came in to deliver them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 We'd go - I used to go up the burn, I used to - have to deliver up the burn and down at Castletown. All walking everywhere.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did you have to walk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Were there many of you doing this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Two of us, that's all.;
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Was this a new job created at this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Well it was just that these two g
irls - us girls used to - was just to fill in the gap until the boys were ready to come back. Until they got the boys back from the war or - or - you know, replaced those who'd lost - they'd lost.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 So this was a boys job before?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 This was a boys j
ob, yes. Yes. Must have been 1920 'cos I remember - taking the telegram on board, because I remember going on - on board evening time. It was dusk, and I had - try and - you know, the wind and that, and the ship was up here somewhere and I was down here. 
A
nd I used to have to try and get them - attract attention to the - people that were on guard sort of thing, and - man came down the ladder, rope ladder, and he said, who's the telegram for? And I said, the Captain of the ship. And he said, oh he's at the 
Kings Arms. That was in - Chivell. Had to go across the Kings Arms. I remember it was misty and nasty and you know. Remember quite well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 What sort of pay did you get for this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Oh - it was very good pay really. I used to get about - eighteen, nineteen shillings a week which was good then you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Was this the reason that you changed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Well I suppose really I was interested, I wanted to do it and that's all there was to it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 What did your parents think?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Well they - they didn't say much, they said - well, if you want to do it}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7880012\charrsid16449734 
, if it - you see, I was very a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 n}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7880012\charrsid16449734 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
emic and it was just the job for me, I - outd}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7880012\charrsid16449734 oors all the time. I was very a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 n}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid7880012\charrsid16449734 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 emic when I was young. Noel Barton tied me to the sorting - to the sorting table, tied me to the l
eg. And the Post Mistress, Miss Rohal come down and she said, girl, Gail, Gail, bell's ringing. And I couldn't get out and she said, she come in and she said, who did this, who did this? She used to talk ever so quick. So I said, Len Baker. I'll give him 
Len Baker she said. She untied me but - telegram was delayed so when he - when he come in he got into trouble for tying me up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 So you worked until about 1920 as a telegram girl, and you were married when you were twenty-one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 So that was about 1925 so you had about five years with the Comlins?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Well I should - yes, about that I should think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did you stop work then when you got married?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Yes. We married in twenty - nineteen - in November 1925.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did you work again after that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No, I never went to work after that. I never went to work until I came back from South Africa.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Then where did you go?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Went to Canterbury.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 What sort of jobs did you do then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 I was married, went in quarters there. And - my - when I came - home - I went back to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Canterbury{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}, we were - I was in rooms at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Canterbury{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 and I went back in quarters. And from there I went from - a place called - where did I go - Shorncliffe, went to Shorncliffe. And Shorncliffe to Borden. And from Borden to {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname 
country-region}}India{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}. India back to Lydd. From Lydd to - Palestine. Palestine to South Africa and back.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 But you didn't work again until after your husband had died?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No. He's not dead. No. Yes, we parted. No, well I haven't - not work until I came back from 
South Africa and then - I got a job - nurse for the kiddies. Although - 'cos I didn't know where he was, I had no money you see, so I had to get a job.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 You got a job doing housework again?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 I went into the - into - hospital doing the - the - sis
ters cubicles. Cleaning. Then - I was redundant from there because - they wanted me to do full time and I - I was only doing part time and I said I couldn't do full time because of the children you see. They said, well - we - we're not employing - part ti
me workers so - had to go. And I was out just a week and I went up }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7880012\charrsid16449734 Pennsylvania}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734  Castle there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 You've done a good selection of jobs haven't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 So before 1918 you really did just housework?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Oh yes, yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Would you really have preferred any other type of work do you think?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
No, I don't know. I don't think I would liked office work. I don't think I'd like to be cooped up in an office. I would have liked to have had some outdoor work if I could have got it you know, I do
n't know what there would have been - outdoor, but I really enjoyed when I was on telegrams, I really enjoyed - being out all the time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 When you finished Mrs Reed's was there any sort of job you wanted to do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No I don't think so, no. There was no alternative but to go back to housework again you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Was there really any alternative on Portland for girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No, either that or shops. Selling in shops and that and that didn't appeal to me. I would - I should hate to be stuck behind a coun
ter - serving.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did your life at home alter after you actually started work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Were you allowed out more?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Well - I was allowed out - won't laugh when I tell you but - I was nearly married - and I went in at eleven o'clock one night. 
And my mum said - you know they used to have the lamps don't you, there was no electric on. And the lamp was turned down low, and she said, that you Evelyn? I said, yes mummy. She said, you tell Bill Cross if he can't keep you - bring you in earlier than 
this to keep away. I was nearly married then. It was eleven o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 How old were you when you met your husband?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 About - nineteen I suppose.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did starting going out to work change your relationship with your parents at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Or with your brothers and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No, no, didn't make any difference. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did you give your wage to your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Well part of it. There wasn't much to - 'cos I had to buy my own clothes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did you give it all and then have some back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
Yes. My mum used to give us - well, you see, what we used to do was - whatever we had we used to hand over. And then - she'd give us whatever she thought, you know, help us over the week, 'cs we didn't really need a lot because there was nowhere to 
go. And - then when we wanted any clothes she used to - help us out with that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did you go out more in the evenings or do anything differently?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Well now, I - I used - never used to go out very much because - well there was nowhere to go, I used t
o go out with - the girls and go on the top of the hills with the boys you know, having a bit of fun and that, and - but I had to be in early. I had to be in - about nine o'clock when I - even when I was working. No question of coming in late, else you ge
t - mum used to say, I'm not putting up with this. Not so many hidings but -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Were you allowed out a bit later once you started work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Well, yes, about half past nine I suppose, but ten o'clock was - if you were out after ten o'clock it was a crime.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did you make any new friends at this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No - no. }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7880012\charrsid16449734 Al}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 l the same ones, same friends, yes. Same people, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did you have any special friends at this time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Yes, I used to have a girlfriend name of Kitty King. And - she used to - come
 - U used to go down to her house and she used to come up to me. Not every night, we weren't - I wasn't allowed out every night, my mother used to say, it's time you stopped in and did so and so and so and so you know. And - but she used to come up - to s
e
e me sometimes and we'd go for a walk but we - we used to go up round - all along on top of the hill and back again and - we never used to do anything very hectic you know. 'Cos there wasn't - well there wasn't very much to do. I used to go dancing a lot 
and I remember once - my mum said - I - she used to go to - she was a - learning to be a tailoress, well that didn't appeal to me 'cos I could have gone, but I couldn't sit sewing all day long. I wanted to do something more, you know, outdoor life. And -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Who was learning to be a tailoress?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
Kitty. And - she - she said, there's a dance down Congers tonight, that's the little chapel down the bottom of the hill, you know, when you go down. So I said, well I don't think I'll be able - be able to come. 
She said, well, I'm going to put my black - she said, I can't go really, she said, but I'm going to put my - black dress, me long dress underneath me }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2847883\charrsid16449734 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734  work}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2847883\charrsid16449734 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
dress, and I - I did the same but - I got caught out, my mum said to me, I thought as much, she sai
d. But that was - that - they were nice little does, I mean, they were - they were - weren't rough, and there were boys and girls about our own age, and we used to have whale of a time really. All tin pop music you know. Not worth anything. But - it reall
y went with a swing and we really enjoyed it. But - and you - you don't - they were dances, they were really dances. I man, not - jigging about like they are now, ballroom dancing and that and of}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2847883\charrsid16449734  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 course I - I went to the drill hall when I was young and - went dancing up there and - I - yes, I - I had to be in by {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 11}}}eleven o'clock{\*\xmlclose}, and - that was - extension you see. And - if I wasn't in by {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}
{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 11}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}{\xmlattrvalue 0}}}eleven o'clock{\*\xmlclose} I wasn't allowed out anymore all the week or perhaps a fortnight.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 How old were you when you went to the drill hall?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Oh about - sixteen, seventeen I think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Who organized the dances up there then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
I don't know - Bunny Whit's Band and that, that was a fellow - under the hill. We had a good, there was beautiful floor for dancing. Used to have a
 smashing time. I used to go with all the boys on the top of the hill you know, about my own age. We used to all meet up there. And then -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 It's sort of middle ground isn't it, half way between?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Yes, that's right, and - there used to be a boy tha
t I was very very fond of, Phil, and he'd say, do I walk you home Evelyn? And I'd say, you walk me to the top of Old Hill then I would run like anything to make it at {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname time}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Minute}
{\xmlattrvalue 0}}{\xmlattr\xmlattrns0{\xmlattrname Hour}{\xmlattrvalue 11}}}eleven o'clock{\*\xmlclose}. 'Cos I was late.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did you know the boys and girls of your own age up at Top Hill?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
Oh gosh, knew all of them. Well we used to come under the hill you see, I mean - as I told you before I mean - Sunday nights, all the boys and girls used to come down there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 They would have gone to school on Top Hill?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Oh yes, they were - but this Lyril that I used to - know very well he used to go to}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid2847883\charrsid16449734  the engineering school in {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Weym}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 outh{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
. Like a secondary school but it was engineering school for boys. And he went there. Very nice boy, but - he married a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2847883\charrsid16449734 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734  under}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2847883\charrsid16449734 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 hill girl.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did you have any contact with any of the Navy people or the soldiers when you were about sixteen or seventeen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Well no, not really. I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did they go to the local dances?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Oh they'd go to local dances, yes, but - I mean - they use
d to go dancing and - but they only - they had their own girlfriends you know I mean to say - we were - our locals you know, the boys and girls and that, we used to dance together and there was - the - the soldiers or the sailors, they used to have their 
- Top Hill girls or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 They'd go with the Top Hill girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
Oh yes. Top hill, from some from under the hill but not very often, you'd - quite a lot of sailors, they'd pick up with the top hill girls, they'd walk 'em home from - th
en they'd meet them again next week you know. That's how it went on. But that was the only - that was the only entertainment then you see, dancing and - or the pictures, they used to go to the pictures but - I wasn't very fond of pictures, I never used to
 like pictures very much.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Was there much trouble with the sailors and soldiers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No, very very little. Very little.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did your parents mind you mixing with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Oh my - my people, they didn't - go very much on it, you know. If - when I w
ent out with a soldier, oh, they said, oh, couldn't you find a {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Portland{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 boy or something like that. I never used to worry, I used to - look after myself and - that was that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did you meet your husband up here?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No, I met my husband - down - some sports, down at the bottom there. I was engaged to a {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}
{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Portland{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
 - to a soldier before I got married. And - Bill Cross came across and he said - are you - Evelyn? And I said, yes. Oh, he said, I'm Billy. I said, very nice. So - I said - he said, can I walk you
 home? I said, well there's plenty of room for both of us. I suppose I was ever so sarcastic. Walked to the bottom of Verne Hill and he said, can I see you tomorrow night? I said, no. He said, I know you're engaged to Billy Pratt, he said, but you'll neve
r marry him. You'll never marry him, and, he said, I said, well we'll wait and see won't we. And he said, yes. And I never did see. Ever so sarcastic I was to him. I says, there's plenty of room for both of us isn't there. He often reminded me about it.

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 What did your husband do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 He was in the Navy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 What sort of job was it, do you know?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 What do you }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2847883\charrsid16449734 mean, in the Navy? Oh - an Asec }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 rating, what they call an asdec rating, that's to do with the - I don't know quite. Now - Joe - I don't know - he just kept home going I suppose, he stayed home all the time. Worked in the dockyard, Joe did.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 What sort of jobs did he do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Labouring. Steel labourer he was. He didn't do anything, you know - yes, he was skilled labourer, yes, what they cal
l a skilled labourer. Now - who was next? Harry. Now Harry was a telegram boy, a postman - in Weymouth.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 He worked on to be a postman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Oh yes, on to a postman and then inspector after that. He got up to inspector. And - Iris -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Inspector in the postal service?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
Yes. And Iris, she - she was a cashier and - she worked in Newman's - the - grocers shop, and from Newman's she went to - was cashier. And then he got married. Marion.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 What did her husband do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 He was - he was a steward in the Navy. {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Marion{\*\xmlclose}
{\*\xmlclose}. I don't - {\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname place}}{\*\xmlopen\xmlns2{\factoidname City}}Marion{\*\xmlclose}{\*\xmlclose}
