 had some decent job - he's very clever, he - he was in the Merchant Navy when she met him you see, and he was a - a donkey greaser, well - it's - tha}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid2847883\charrsid16449734 t}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 's a good job in the - in the Merchant Navy. And - he came out of there and - I don't know what he did, h
e did sort - all sorts of jobs and then of course this trouble started. Well then he went down to Plymouth, and this woman that he married - was supposed to have been sterilized, and she had a twin. Was on - she's been on television. And - well, dear oh d
e
ar, well anyway, she wrote to the Welfare people in Plymouth, and the - letter came back, Mr Walker is no longer employed in the Admiralty, so he'd got the sack from somewhere else. 'Cos he's a proper rogue, he - I mean - I - I don't know, I can't swear a
n
d I can't - accuse, but I had my gas meter robbed, and I reckon he did it. See, but I couldn't point - pin-point it and I couldn't say. I mean - I've got my own ideas and that. So that's the type of man he is you see, so I say she's far better without him
. It's hard lines that she's got to work and keep the kiddies, 'cos I mean -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 The social security can reclaim the money rather than the wife having to do it
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Yes, but the thing is you see - they say well you've got a son working, you've got two son
s working. They take - they don't take - they don't take it into consideration that they've got to be kept, it's money coming in the house, you see. And - I was going to say that - so she can't - he's unemployed so therefore she can't get any money from h
im.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 I suppose she's got almost up to the Social Security limit coming in from the two boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
Yes. Well she shouldn't have to go to work. 'Cos she's got - there's Kim and there's Nicholas and there's Helen to be kept and Alan. Alan started a job at
 - in Weymouth, he'd just left school, and - Alan - he was on a month's trial you see, and they went to see the manager and he said, I'm afraid he won't be any good because of his feet. He's got something wrong with his feet - he cripples. And - and Annet
e
 made an appointment to see the Doctor last Friday at quarter past six and he was nowhere to be found. See? So - anyway, she could quite see the point, the man said, he's a very willing worker, he's a good worker, he said, but come on the busy season, he 
s
aid, we shan't be able to employ him. So - Annette said to him - a real good living girl you know, she wouldn't hurt anybody not for worlds, but I'm afraid I was a little bit rougher than that and a little bit - I wasn't going to be trod on or sat on and 
nobody was going to do what they liked with me. So that was that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did you actually have your meals with Mrs Reed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No, no. On my own. Oh yes. In the kitchen. In the kitchen, she had hers in the dining room.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did you actually have the same food?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
I don't know, if I did I don't know. All I know is what I have. I had - in the mornings I used to - she used to give me a piece of bread and butter and jam or marmalade and a cup of tea. For my breakfast. That's all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 What time would you have your breakfast then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 About half past seven.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 You'd get there and do some work and then have your breakfast?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Then have our breakfast, yes. And she - she'd be cooking - she'd be booking the girls breakfast about eight o'clock you see and then -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 How old were the girls then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
Oh they were grown up. One was a schoolteacher in Weymouth and the other one was Civil Servant, they were - quite young women you know. Mathilda and Nancy their names were.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 What about when you worked for the people in the china shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 What time did I have to get there? Nine o'clock.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 In what way was it different there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Oh I was only working there from - from nine 'til twelve, nine to - no, nine 'til one. I wasn't working full time there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 This was only part time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 YES.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Why did you take a part time job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Well I suppose that - that's all they could afford to pay you see I mean - I don't - I - I think I got about ten shillings there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Was this because you couldn't get another job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
Well there was nothing else about you see. Not part time, I could get plenty of - jobs living in - service. You know, like - housemaid or that, and I remember once - I don't know, we - I couldn't have been very old, I wasn't old, Ida and I, we w
ere going to Fleet. She was going to be the cook and I was going to be the nursemaid. We went there - and when the nurse - when the - lady of the house came - she said to Ida she said, how old is she. Ida did say, I wasn't very old. She said, can she take
 complete charge - child - charge of a - a young baby. Oh yes, she said, she can do it. We never got the job though.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 How old were you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 I couldn't have been very old. But I - I - I could have taken the child on - you know - because I'd been 
brought up with children, you see. I couldn't have been very old. And we laughed about that. Never materialized though.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 This was when you were supposed to be looking for another job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Job, that's right yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 You said you could have got plenty of jobs living in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
Living in. Yes. Domestic, housemaids, or something like that but - I - I wasn't going to have that. Because - you see - it was a case of - if you lived in - you were up early in the morning and you were on right until - night time
. I mean - now I had a - a cousin that was in service, and she was working - up until ten o'clock at night some nights. And getting only about - I suppose about fifteen shillings a week. Well - I wasn't going to do that. Not for anybody. 'Cos - once you'r
e
 in you see you're in and you're there, they want you you're there. And it was a case of working then, it wasn't a case like it is now, you see they can't get girls. Now I know someone under the hill now who's been in - been in hospital very ill and - she
 
came to - well, she sent for me and she asked me if I would help her out. I said, I'm very sorry, but I've got full time now, I can't do anything. Can't get anybody to do anything for - love nor money. She shouldn't really be home, she should have been - 
still been in hospital 'cos she - she'}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11149907\charrsid16449734 s - something to do with arthrit}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
is in the spine she's got. And - she said, oh she could get somebody to help her and she could do - her neighbours would do - yes, but you can't depend on neighbours all the time. I mean it's a tie.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did you have a row with your mother about this, when you were looking for another job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
Oh over - over leaving Mrs Reed. Oh no. Oh no, no. Well she knew as well as I did that there was anything - I mean, she wouldn't let me go and sleep in anywhere because it was too hard work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did your mother actually say she didn't want you to do this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Well she didn't exactly - in as much as say she didn't want me to do it, but she said, it was very hard work for a young girl.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 So did your parents just keep you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
Well - between times when I could get a job she - they had - well we more or less - I worked at home see, I did the work at home and so it was just the - same really.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did your mother try and get you jobs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Oh yes. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Or was it up to you to try and get a job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
Well, it was - both ways, I mean, if she heard of anything there you are, I was there. And if not, if I went - heard of anything going - there was no - no question of advertising you see. You just had to - do the best you could. Hearsay sort of thing.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 What kind of things did you have to do when you went down to the china shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Well - nine 'til twelve. Well - I used to - she - invariably have her breakfast and I used to wash up her
 breakfast things. And - go up and do the - top rooms and the - the bedroom and the sitting room and that, the sitting room was behind the shop and the bedroom and - then if she wanted to slip out then I would listen you know and - be in the shop. But I w
as in the house more than I was in the shop. It wasn't a case - I wasn't engaged for the shop.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did they have any children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 They had one - two boys, one was Jim and the other one was - Billy.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Were you engaged to do anything for them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No. No. No. Not at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Your duties were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
In the house and you know - cleaning that's right. Not even cooking there I didn't do any. When I was in Mrs Coalnuts, it - I was there during one Christmas you know. And - she came to me Christmas morning
 and she said, Evelyn, I'm going to learn - leave you to turn - cook the turkey. Oh gosh, I thought to myself, here comes. Well I - I - I'd done cooking, you know, at home, but - nothing like that. I thought to myself, well am I going to do, I - I don't k
n
ow anything about this. She said, I'll tell you what to do. So she told me and I did it. She came back from church and believe you me I was never more pleased to see anybody come back than I was her. So she looked and she said it was done to perfection. A
nd - after that I thought to myself - that gave me such confidence I could cook anything. He was the clerk to the council, her husband.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Was this before you were a telegram girl or after?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Yes. I can't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 What sort of job were you doing there then?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Cleaning. Cleaning.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Were you doing full hours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
Only part time. Nine 'til - three. I used to go down there at nine and - wash up the breakfast things, and make the beds. And then - I used to - come down and - Mondays I used to
 help her do her washing and - rinse it and - she used to hang it out, we used to work together sort thing you know, in that respect. Well the - then there was - there was two rooms downstairs and three rooms upstairs - four rooms upstairs. And I used to 
d
o them - you know, like alternately. Clean the windows and - everything in general there. She had two - she had three children - two girls and a boy, Edgar - was a - he - he turned out to be a schoolmaster. Freda, she went to secondary school - she landed
 up serving behind a - in a - in the - in a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11149907\charrsid16449734 dra}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
per's shop, in the counter. And Doris was still - was still going to school when I was there. She was only young.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Did you have to do anything for her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 When you were working part time for these people did you see them outside your working hours?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Oh no, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
I THINK - this applies to people living in, whether the people they were working for had any real affect on their lives and their attitudes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Oh no. No. Oh no, no, I 
don't - all I know is that they used to - have a half day. And every other Sunday off. And that was the - usual - thing for - girls living in. You know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 What did he do for a living?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 He - he was a Clerk to the council.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 So they had quite a big house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Well where Doctor - Brody lives. Lived.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Were you the only servant there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 So these were fairly small houses?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 Houses, yes. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid12858205 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 It must have been a fairly personal relationship then, not a sort of servant relationship?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid4735342 EC  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 No, no. I used to have my meals with them. Sit down with meals and that because Mr }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid11149907\charrsid16449734 C}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid11080425\charrsid16449734 
oalnut - you see - he used to like to have - lunchtimes he used to like to - look at his paper, you know, and - up on the dresser there's a huge jug and he u
sed to say, Evelyn, like that to me you see and I used to get the jug down and put it front of him, prop his paper up and she used to say, Evelyn - you're worse than Mr Coalnut. You encourage him.
\par }}